1
00:00:41,100 --> 00:00:42,397
<i>TOMAR-RE:
Billions of years ago...</i>

2
00:00:42,568 --> 00:00:47,232
<i>... a race of immortals harnessed
the most powerful force in existence:</i>

3
00:00:47,506 --> 00:00:50,873
<i>The emerald energy of willpower.</i>

4
00:00:51,043 --> 00:00:53,443
<i>These immortals,
the Guardians of the Universe...</i>

5
00:00:53,613 --> 00:00:56,980
<i>... built a world from where they could
watch over all of existence:</i>

6
00:00:57,149 --> 00:00:59,549
<i>The planet Oa.</i>

7
00:01:00,386 --> 00:01:04,618
<i>They divided the universe
into 3600 sectors.</i>

8
00:01:04,790 --> 00:01:10,285
<i>A ring powered by the energy of will
was sent to every sector to select a recruit.</i>

9
00:01:10,963 --> 00:01:15,832
<i>In order to be chosen by the ring,
it was said one must be without fear.</i>

10
00:01:16,836 --> 00:01:18,963
<i>Together, these 3600 recruits...</i>

11
00:01:19,138 --> 00:01:25,099
<i>... formed the intergalactic peacekeepers
known as the Green Lantern Corps.</i>

12
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:36,813
<i>Of all the threats the Corps ever faced...</i>

13
00:01:36,989 --> 00:01:41,153
<i>... the gravest was an entity of fear
known as Parallax.</i>

14
00:01:41,594 --> 00:01:43,892
<i>Only the legendary Green Lantern
Abin Sur...</i>

15
00:01:44,063 --> 00:01:47,396
<i>... was capable of capturing
and imprisoning this beast...</i>

16
00:01:47,566 --> 00:01:51,332
<i>... which he did on the lost planet of Ryut.</i>

17
00:02:10,423 --> 00:02:15,224
COMMANDER [IN ALIEN LANGUAGE]:

18
00:02:40,653 --> 00:02:43,918
[ALL YELLING]

19
00:02:49,462 --> 00:02:52,454
[ALL GRUNTING]

20
00:03:04,777 --> 00:03:07,769
[ALL GASPING]

21
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:17,112
[ALL YELLING]

22
00:03:19,592 --> 00:03:21,822
You are afraid.

23
00:03:21,994 --> 00:03:23,928
Good.

24
00:03:24,096 --> 00:03:27,088
[ROARS]

25
00:03:30,503 --> 00:03:33,495
[ALL SCREAMING]

26
00:03:47,353 --> 00:03:49,150
[ROARS]

27
00:04:52,885 --> 00:04:54,318
[BEEPING]

28
00:05:01,594 --> 00:05:06,054
Sinestro, I'm traveling at maximum velocity.
Tell Fentara I should...

29
00:05:06,232 --> 00:05:07,699
<i>Fentara is dead.</i>

30
00:05:10,536 --> 00:05:12,265
The planet's inhabitants?

31
00:05:12,438 --> 00:05:14,872
<i>Your mission to evacuate them
is no longer necessary.</i>

32
00:05:15,474 --> 00:05:17,499
<i>It's just as it was on Talok.</i>

33
00:05:17,943 --> 00:05:20,912
<i>Every life form destroyed
and their essence absorbed.</i>

34
00:05:21,347 --> 00:05:23,247
<i>Traces of yellow power everywhere.</i>

35
00:05:23,415 --> 00:05:24,746
And the Guardians?

36
00:05:24,917 --> 00:05:27,385
<i>The Guardians are silent.</i>

37
00:05:27,686 --> 00:05:29,586
<i>I've demanded an audience with them.</i>

38
00:05:32,191 --> 00:05:35,388
[RING BEEPING]

39
00:05:38,364 --> 00:05:40,730
PARALLAX:
Abin Sur.

40
00:05:42,434 --> 00:05:45,767
[ABIN SUR GRUNTING]

41
00:05:48,707 --> 00:05:51,073
[PARALLAX GROWLING]

42
00:05:58,918 --> 00:06:00,215
[PARALLAX GROWLS]

43
00:06:19,838 --> 00:06:22,102
[PANTING]

44
00:06:32,751 --> 00:06:33,945
ABIN SUR:
I'm badly wounded.

45
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:39,022
Heading to the nearest inhabited planet
for the selection process.

46
00:06:39,191 --> 00:06:42,957
Tell the Guardians it's Parallax.

47
00:06:48,067 --> 00:06:49,864
[BOTH GRUNT]

48
00:06:51,804 --> 00:06:52,930
[CLOCK CLICKS]

49
00:06:57,476 --> 00:07:00,001
No. No.

50
00:07:06,452 --> 00:07:08,682
Sorry, I gotta run.
Make yourself at home, okay?

51
00:07:08,854 --> 00:07:10,617
There's, uh, water in the tap.

52
00:07:35,714 --> 00:07:36,976
HAL:
No!

53
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:38,808
Yup.

54
00:07:38,984 --> 00:07:41,976
[TRUCK HORN HONKING]

55
00:07:44,089 --> 00:07:45,351
Asshole.

56
00:07:46,725 --> 00:07:52,027
MAN: The Ferris Sabre III is state-of-the-art
of artificial-intelligence fighter planes.

57
00:07:52,197 --> 00:07:56,031
It has all of the flying and combat
capability of a human pilot...

58
00:07:56,502 --> 00:07:59,335
...but with none of the human error
that comes with it.

59
00:07:59,772 --> 00:08:02,502
Carl isn't just blowing smoke
to get a contract, general.

60
00:08:02,675 --> 00:08:04,700
Your staff, these contractors, my office...

61
00:08:04,877 --> 00:08:07,277
...we've all been part of this
from the ground up.

62
00:08:07,613 --> 00:08:09,240
Well, I appreciate that, senator.

63
00:08:09,415 --> 00:08:11,508
HAMMOND:
But today the rubber meets the road.

64
00:08:11,684 --> 00:08:16,678
We have a simulated combat situation.
Two Sabres against Carl's two best pilots.

65
00:08:17,222 --> 00:08:20,020
[CAR HORN HONKING]

66
00:08:30,269 --> 00:08:33,295
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

67
00:08:33,472 --> 00:08:36,305
Carol. Was gonna do a little flying today.
What do you think?

68
00:08:36,475 --> 00:08:37,703
I think you're late.

69
00:08:37,876 --> 00:08:39,935
Yes, but that's only because I slept in.

70
00:08:40,112 --> 00:08:42,103
I used to sleep in. Then I turned 11.

71
00:08:42,548 --> 00:08:44,175
Let me give you a little heads-up.

72
00:08:44,349 --> 00:08:47,750
I've gone up against these Sabres all week
and they smoked me every time.

73
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:51,321
There isn't anything you can do that
they can't do better, faster...

74
00:08:51,490 --> 00:08:53,754
...and without disappointing women
everywhere.

75
00:08:53,926 --> 00:08:56,326
I, uh, think we both know that's not true.

76
00:08:56,495 --> 00:08:59,896
This is exactly why I didn't want you
for this. My father did.

77
00:09:00,065 --> 00:09:01,498
I would've gone with Jensen.

78
00:09:01,667 --> 00:09:05,330
I'd have too, but unfortunately
he's busy not being good enough.

79
00:09:05,504 --> 00:09:07,028
At least he shows up.

80
00:09:07,206 --> 00:09:08,696
Hal...

81
00:09:08,874 --> 00:09:10,842
...this test today, it's important.

82
00:09:11,009 --> 00:09:13,842
I'm gonna make you look good up there.
Don't worry, okay?

83
00:09:14,012 --> 00:09:17,607
Now let's get these pants off
and fly some planes.

84
00:09:21,253 --> 00:09:22,515
Highball, weapon check now.

85
00:09:22,688 --> 00:09:23,985
Roger that.

86
00:09:26,992 --> 00:09:29,119
TOM: Good morning, Mr. Ferris.
CARL: Morning, everybody.

87
00:09:30,829 --> 00:09:31,853
Gentlemen.

88
00:09:32,798 --> 00:09:36,359
- We about ready, Tom?
- Yes, Mr. Ferris. We are go for test.

89
00:09:36,902 --> 00:09:39,530
Sapphire, cleared weapons hot
at the merge.

90
00:09:39,705 --> 00:09:42,299
Ferris Test, Sapphire. Weapons are hot.

91
00:09:42,474 --> 00:09:44,271
Fly safe, Highball.

92
00:09:44,443 --> 00:09:46,536
HAL:
Um, no.

93
00:09:57,322 --> 00:10:00,189
Goddamn it!
Tom, what the hell you feed those things?

94
00:10:00,626 --> 00:10:02,059
F-35s, what else?

95
00:10:02,227 --> 00:10:03,285
[CARL CHUCKLING]

96
00:10:09,401 --> 00:10:11,164
<i>HAL [OVER RADIO]:
Wakey, wakey, Sapphire.</i>

97
00:10:11,336 --> 00:10:13,327
You got a shot,
now would be a great time.

98
00:10:13,505 --> 00:10:16,440
Easy, Highball. Just lining it up.

99
00:10:24,817 --> 00:10:26,614
[BEEPING]

100
00:10:30,322 --> 00:10:32,552
There's no way
we're taking these out solo.

101
00:10:32,724 --> 00:10:34,988
<i>Get over here.
Let's figure something out.</i>

102
00:10:35,594 --> 00:10:37,494
<i>CAROL [OVER RADIO]:
On my way, Highball.</i>

103
00:10:42,234 --> 00:10:45,169
HAL:
Now stay right there and look real pretty.

104
00:10:54,613 --> 00:10:57,514
[GRUNTING]

105
00:10:58,951 --> 00:11:01,351
[BEEPING]

106
00:11:03,689 --> 00:11:05,122
[GRUNTS]

107
00:11:08,460 --> 00:11:10,860
Highball, did you just use your wingman
as a decoy?

108
00:11:11,029 --> 00:11:12,394
[LAUGHING]

109
00:11:33,051 --> 00:11:36,987
Highball, those Sabres headed up your 6
can fly anywhere you can.

110
00:11:37,155 --> 00:11:39,055
Then let's go somewhere I can't fly.

111
00:11:43,028 --> 00:11:45,053
What the hell is he up to?

112
00:11:45,564 --> 00:11:46,588
Coffin corner.

113
00:11:47,699 --> 00:11:51,499
Highball, rules of engagement
set ceiling at 50,000 feet.

114
00:11:51,670 --> 00:11:54,935
HAL: Yeah, because the Sabres will stall
if they go any higher, right, Tom?

115
00:11:55,107 --> 00:11:56,301
And so will you.

116
00:12:02,281 --> 00:12:04,647
<i>COMPUTER:
Compressor stall. Compressor stall.</i>

117
00:12:04,816 --> 00:12:05,942
[ALARM BLARING]

118
00:12:17,162 --> 00:12:18,595
[GASPS]

119
00:12:24,036 --> 00:12:25,367
[PANTING]

120
00:12:28,941 --> 00:12:30,772
[BEEPING]

121
00:12:37,449 --> 00:12:39,007
[BEEPING]

122
00:12:42,454 --> 00:12:43,716
Yes!

123
00:12:46,792 --> 00:12:47,952
[TOM CLEARS THROAT]

124
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:51,529
Um, I mean, damn it, Hal.

125
00:12:51,964 --> 00:12:54,330
Your boy certainly
takes his job seriously.

126
00:12:56,001 --> 00:12:57,969
<i>TOM [OVER RADIO]:
Ailerons, Hal. Side to side.</i>

127
00:12:58,136 --> 00:12:59,160
I got it.

128
00:12:59,338 --> 00:13:02,034
[ALARM BLARING]

129
00:13:03,608 --> 00:13:04,632
<i>MARTIN:
Hal.</i>

130
00:13:10,115 --> 00:13:11,582
Keep it warm for me.

131
00:13:13,819 --> 00:13:15,343
TECHNICIAN:
Going through 25,000.

132
00:13:16,455 --> 00:13:17,752
Hey, you okay, Highball?

133
00:13:18,790 --> 00:13:20,553
Yeah, just taking my victory lap.

134
00:13:25,530 --> 00:13:27,896
[GRUNTING]

135
00:13:28,066 --> 00:13:30,899
TECHNICIAN: Going through 20,000.
- Okay, Highball, give me some roll.

136
00:13:37,042 --> 00:13:38,304
[CHEERS]

137
00:13:38,477 --> 00:13:39,705
Yeah, Dad!

138
00:13:40,912 --> 00:13:42,379
<i>TOM:
Hal, do you read me?</i>

139
00:13:45,217 --> 00:13:46,775
[GASPS]

140
00:13:52,024 --> 00:13:55,084
<i>TOM: Highball, you're approaching
minimum ejection altitude.</i>

141
00:13:59,998 --> 00:14:02,933
<i>Highball, you're below 10,000 AGL.
Spin is unrecoverable.</i>

142
00:14:03,368 --> 00:14:05,529
<i>Eject, eject, eject!</i>

143
00:14:06,571 --> 00:14:08,698
You're not scared, are you, Dad?

144
00:14:09,307 --> 00:14:11,707
Let's just say it's my job not to be.

145
00:14:17,783 --> 00:14:18,807
HAL:
Dad!

146
00:14:22,421 --> 00:14:23,718
Dad!

147
00:14:24,556 --> 00:14:25,648
[GRUNTS]

148
00:14:26,158 --> 00:14:27,887
[GRUNTING]

149
00:14:32,831 --> 00:14:35,823
[GASPING]

150
00:14:43,608 --> 00:14:45,303
You stupid son of a bitch. You...

151
00:14:45,477 --> 00:14:47,536
CARL:
Stand down, Bob. It doesn't matter now.

152
00:14:47,712 --> 00:14:48,872
It does matter.

153
00:14:49,047 --> 00:14:51,948
Never mind that you crashed
a brand-new F-35.

154
00:14:52,117 --> 00:14:55,018
You broke the rules of engagement.
You sacrificed your wingman.

155
00:14:55,187 --> 00:14:57,781
And you blew the contract
this company was depending on.

156
00:14:57,956 --> 00:14:59,924
I'm sorry. I thought this was a dogfight.

157
00:15:00,092 --> 00:15:02,583
I was under the impression
the objective was to win.

158
00:15:02,761 --> 00:15:05,821
No, the objective was to show
what the Sabres could do in combat.

159
00:15:05,997 --> 00:15:08,966
And in combat,
no pilot is gonna crater his own plane.

160
00:15:09,768 --> 00:15:10,792
I did.

161
00:15:11,736 --> 00:15:15,365
Now you know you gotta boost the ceiling.
I showed you what they can't do.

162
00:15:15,540 --> 00:15:18,202
You didn't have to make that point
in front of Air Force Acquisitions.

163
00:15:18,376 --> 00:15:19,604
That's enough, Carol.

164
00:15:21,446 --> 00:15:25,314
Since I'm gonna have to lay off most of
my company anyway, you're fired, Hal.

165
00:15:25,484 --> 00:15:26,610
It's too late. I quit.

166
00:15:26,785 --> 00:15:28,412
CAROL:
He's not fired and you don't quit.

167
00:15:28,587 --> 00:15:31,215
You're grounded,
pending the results of an investigation.

168
00:15:38,463 --> 00:15:40,397
Watch your back.

169
00:15:40,599 --> 00:15:41,998
That's impossible, Bob.

170
00:15:49,307 --> 00:15:51,366
- Tell me what happened.
- Controls locked up.

171
00:15:51,543 --> 00:15:54,979
Don't give me that, Hal. You had a
window when you could've recovered.

172
00:15:55,147 --> 00:15:56,671
Did you choke?

173
00:15:56,848 --> 00:15:58,975
You wouldn't be the first,
but I need to know.

174
00:15:59,151 --> 00:16:01,847
My controls locked up.
What the hell is all this, anyway?

175
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:03,510
What's with the ridiculous suit?

176
00:16:03,688 --> 00:16:07,454
- I know your dad's been bucking for you...
- The merits of my career choices...

177
00:16:07,626 --> 00:16:11,824
You're a pilot, and a good one.
Giving that up to fly a desk is bullshit.

178
00:16:11,997 --> 00:16:13,328
I like it and I'm good at it.

179
00:16:13,498 --> 00:16:17,195
Doesn't mean I'll never get in a cockpit
again. It isn't one way or the other.

180
00:16:17,369 --> 00:16:20,805
That's the way a child looks at things,
and we aren't children anymore.

181
00:16:22,574 --> 00:16:23,836
At least...

182
00:16:27,946 --> 00:16:31,006
I just don't wanna see
someone I care about getting hurt.

183
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:33,740
Least of all you.

184
00:16:58,276 --> 00:17:01,268
[GRUNTING]

185
00:17:11,856 --> 00:17:14,086
Choose well.

186
00:17:24,569 --> 00:17:27,561
[THE ROSES' "FANCY WOMEN"
PLAYING ON STEREO]

187
00:17:29,374 --> 00:17:30,671
[ENGINE STOPS]

188
00:17:30,842 --> 00:17:33,834
[CHILDREN CHATTERING]

189
00:17:37,616 --> 00:17:41,450
<i>A test pilot's daring maneuvers
almost ended in tragedy.</i>

190
00:17:41,620 --> 00:17:46,080
<i>Witnesses say pilot Hal Jordan
ejected at the last possible second...</i>

191
00:17:46,258 --> 00:17:48,317
<i>... before his jet crashed
in the open desert.</i>

192
00:17:48,493 --> 00:17:50,427
<i>He's the son of the late Martin Jordan...</i>

193
00:17:50,595 --> 00:17:53,621
<i>... who was killed in his own
ill-fated test flight back in 1993.</i>

194
00:17:53,798 --> 00:17:56,323
<i>We are told that Hal Jordan
is doing fine right now...</i>

195
00:17:56,501 --> 00:17:59,368
<i>... though we have yet to hear
an official statement.</i>

196
00:17:59,537 --> 00:18:00,561
Hey, guys.

197
00:18:00,739 --> 00:18:04,300
<i>HEBERT: The incident has been a blow
to a new high-tech aircraft program...</i>

198
00:18:04,476 --> 00:18:05,909
JACK:
Hey. How was work?

199
00:18:06,077 --> 00:18:08,637
Oh. It was amazing, Jack.
Thank you for asking. Hey, Janice.

200
00:18:08,813 --> 00:18:11,941
Just help me out here, because
I'm really trying to understand this.

201
00:18:12,117 --> 00:18:13,982
- Mm-hm.
- Do you wanna be like him so bad?

202
00:18:14,152 --> 00:18:16,416
- You just assume it's my fault.
- I talked to Carl.

203
00:18:16,588 --> 00:18:18,681
- Oh. Heh, heh.
- You pushed the plane past its limits...

204
00:18:18,857 --> 00:18:21,655
That's my job. It was an accident.
Everybody walked away.

205
00:18:21,826 --> 00:18:25,227
Like your motorcycle accident
that put you in the hospital for a month?

206
00:18:25,497 --> 00:18:28,193
I miss all this quality family time.
Good talk, Jack.

207
00:18:28,366 --> 00:18:31,733
JACK: God.
JANICE: Jack, come on.

208
00:18:32,370 --> 00:18:33,564
JIM:
You okay?

209
00:18:34,773 --> 00:18:35,797
Where's Jason?

210
00:18:36,908 --> 00:18:38,273
In his room.

211
00:18:38,443 --> 00:18:39,967
Why?

212
00:18:41,813 --> 00:18:42,837
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

213
00:18:43,014 --> 00:18:44,311
HAL:
Hey, it's Uncle Hal.

214
00:18:45,517 --> 00:18:46,575
What's up there, ace?

215
00:18:46,751 --> 00:18:50,482
This is the worst 11th birthday party
I've ever been to.

216
00:18:50,655 --> 00:18:53,089
No dancing girls?
What's going on...? Hey.

217
00:18:53,992 --> 00:18:55,584
Hey.

218
00:18:56,795 --> 00:18:58,023
I'm fine.

219
00:18:58,196 --> 00:19:00,596
I guess I got a little freaked out
or something.

220
00:19:00,765 --> 00:19:02,630
It happens.

221
00:19:02,834 --> 00:19:03,858
Not to you.

222
00:19:04,302 --> 00:19:05,792
Look...

223
00:19:06,638 --> 00:19:08,663
...you don't have anything
to worry about.

224
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:09,864
You wanna know why?

225
00:19:10,308 --> 00:19:13,869
Yeah, I may be a total screw-up
in every other part of my life...

226
00:19:14,045 --> 00:19:18,072
...but the one thing I do know
how to do is fly.

227
00:19:19,718 --> 00:19:24,655
Hey, got you something, birthday boy.
Wrapped it myself.

228
00:19:30,195 --> 00:19:32,026
Cool. It's an X-1, right?

229
00:19:32,197 --> 00:19:35,257
It's a Starfighter. My dad gave me that.

230
00:19:35,433 --> 00:19:37,094
Let's put it up.

231
00:19:39,337 --> 00:19:40,964
What happened today?

232
00:19:41,139 --> 00:19:42,766
I mean, when you crashed.

233
00:19:42,941 --> 00:19:44,875
HAL:
Not really sure, exactly.

234
00:19:47,011 --> 00:19:48,273
Were you scared?

235
00:19:50,448 --> 00:19:52,143
It's my job not to be.

236
00:19:54,252 --> 00:19:57,653
You know, you're totally missing
your super-lame birthday party.

237
00:19:57,822 --> 00:20:01,383
Beat it. Go, go, go!

238
00:20:03,661 --> 00:20:05,822
I'm glad you're okay.

239
00:20:07,999 --> 00:20:10,058
Me too, ace.

240
00:20:23,081 --> 00:20:24,173
[GRUNTING]

241
00:20:24,349 --> 00:20:25,577
Get off! No!

242
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:30,147
Aah! No!

243
00:20:30,321 --> 00:20:33,415
[YELLING]

244
00:20:38,329 --> 00:20:39,591
[GRUNTS]

245
00:20:39,764 --> 00:20:42,756
[PANTING]

246
00:21:10,628 --> 00:21:12,721
[GRUNTING]

247
00:21:30,582 --> 00:21:31,776
[HAL GRUNTS]

248
00:21:31,950 --> 00:21:35,750
HAL: Come on, stay with me. Stay with me.
I'm gonna get you some help.

249
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:39,412
You're gonna be okay.
You're gonna be okay. Okay, hold on.

250
00:21:39,591 --> 00:21:41,855
Your name. Your name.

251
00:21:42,026 --> 00:21:44,688
It's Hal. Hal Jordan.

252
00:21:44,863 --> 00:21:49,800
Hal Jordan, I am Abin Sur,
protector of Sector 2814.

253
00:21:49,968 --> 00:21:51,196
HAL:
Okay, hey, listen.

254
00:21:51,369 --> 00:21:56,830
We're gonna get you to a hospital, okay?
Okay? One that carries purple blood.

255
00:21:57,008 --> 00:21:58,202
[ABIN SUR GASPING]

256
00:21:58,376 --> 00:21:59,400
ABIN SUR:
The ring...

257
00:21:59,577 --> 00:22:01,101
...it chose you.

258
00:22:01,746 --> 00:22:02,770
Take it!

259
00:22:03,281 --> 00:22:07,183
Place the ring in the lantern.

260
00:22:07,352 --> 00:22:09,912
Place the ring, speak the oath...

261
00:22:10,355 --> 00:22:12,550
- What?
- Great honor, responsibility...

262
00:22:12,724 --> 00:22:15,318
I don't understand.
Breathe. You gotta breathe, okay?

263
00:22:15,493 --> 00:22:17,961
All you gotta do is breathe.
Just breathe, okay?

264
00:22:18,129 --> 00:22:20,597
Hey, hey, hey. No, no, no.
Hey, hey.

265
00:22:21,199 --> 00:22:24,600
Hey, hey, hey. Come on, man.
No, no, no, don't do that.

266
00:22:25,103 --> 00:22:28,561
[STAMMERS]
Hey, now, don't do that.

267
00:22:29,474 --> 00:22:31,442
Oh, come on.

268
00:22:43,855 --> 00:22:47,154
<i>COMPUTER:
X- 97 systems check complete.</i>

269
00:22:47,325 --> 00:22:50,317
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

270
00:22:52,330 --> 00:22:53,797
Yo.

271
00:22:56,367 --> 00:22:57,391
Come again?

272
00:23:05,143 --> 00:23:06,303
[ENGINE STOPS]

273
00:23:15,420 --> 00:23:16,512
Hmm.

274
00:23:17,488 --> 00:23:18,614
Is that a spaceship?

275
00:23:19,057 --> 00:23:20,354
Yeah.

276
00:23:21,659 --> 00:23:22,990
Is it real?

277
00:23:24,095 --> 00:23:25,357
It's real.

278
00:23:25,863 --> 00:23:28,354
Did you see what kind of power source
this thing uses?

279
00:23:28,533 --> 00:23:30,296
- Do you understand...?
- We can't stay.

280
00:23:30,468 --> 00:23:31,730
- We can't stay here.
- What?

281
00:23:31,903 --> 00:23:33,768
- Gotta go.
- What?

282
00:23:34,472 --> 00:23:35,496
HAL:
Pilot.

283
00:23:35,873 --> 00:23:38,774
He wore a uniform.
I think he was a soldier.

284
00:23:38,943 --> 00:23:40,774
He gave me this.

285
00:23:41,446 --> 00:23:42,470
He proposed?

286
00:23:42,647 --> 00:23:45,013
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

287
00:23:47,952 --> 00:23:50,284
We're gone. We're gone, now!

288
00:23:51,623 --> 00:23:53,318
[ENGINE STARTS]

289
00:24:05,803 --> 00:24:09,295
They're gonna know someone was there.
Alien pilots don't bury themselves.

290
00:24:09,474 --> 00:24:11,066
I couldn't just leave him there.

291
00:24:12,076 --> 00:24:13,839
I hope this thing isn't radioactive.

292
00:24:14,445 --> 00:24:17,039
- Yeah, well, you're the genius. You... Aah!
- Aah!

293
00:24:17,215 --> 00:24:18,876
HAL: Jesus!
- Aah! Whoa!

294
00:24:22,153 --> 00:24:23,484
Got it!

295
00:24:24,989 --> 00:24:28,186
He said that the ring chose me.

296
00:24:28,359 --> 00:24:31,726
He said it was a great honor.
Responsibility.

297
00:24:32,196 --> 00:24:33,220
Responsibility?

298
00:24:33,398 --> 00:24:34,422
- Yeah.
- You?

299
00:24:37,235 --> 00:24:40,762
Well, maybe on their planet
"responsibility" just means "asshole."

300
00:24:41,639 --> 00:24:43,197
Let's hope so.

301
00:24:56,654 --> 00:24:59,248
A great light has gone out
in the universe.

302
00:24:59,857 --> 00:25:01,848
Abin Sur is dead.

303
00:25:04,062 --> 00:25:07,520
Four of my Lantern brothers killed.

304
00:25:07,799 --> 00:25:12,133
The inhabitants of two worlds
annihilated by an unknown enemy.

305
00:25:12,303 --> 00:25:15,397
An enemy that possesses
the yellow power of fear.

306
00:25:20,845 --> 00:25:23,336
We know it originated from
within the Lost Sector.

307
00:25:23,514 --> 00:25:26,915
We know it grows more powerful
with each encounter.

308
00:25:27,885 --> 00:25:32,322
According to Abin Sur's last transmission,
he seemed to know what it was.

309
00:25:33,191 --> 00:25:36,388
His only words were, "It's Parallax."

310
00:25:43,034 --> 00:25:46,936
We are aware of the threat.
We are assessing the situation.

311
00:25:48,206 --> 00:25:51,767
While you assess,
innocent lives will be lost.

312
00:25:52,076 --> 00:25:53,839
Let me take the fight to this enemy.

313
00:25:54,011 --> 00:25:57,503
There is much of which
you are not aware, Sinestro.

314
00:25:57,682 --> 00:26:00,412
If the danger is as great as we suspect...

315
00:26:00,585 --> 00:26:02,348
What are you saying?

316
00:26:03,187 --> 00:26:05,781
You believe this enemy can defeat us?

317
00:26:14,866 --> 00:26:19,200
Guardians, if your faith in our power
has faltered, let me renew it.

318
00:26:19,637 --> 00:26:22,970
Let me take a squadron of my strongest
Lanterns against this enemy...

319
00:26:23,141 --> 00:26:27,100
...and I'll prove to you
our best days are not behind us.

320
00:26:47,665 --> 00:26:50,031
[DOORBELL RINGS]

321
00:26:52,970 --> 00:26:55,302
[DOORBELL CONTINUES RINGING]

322
00:27:02,713 --> 00:27:03,771
[KNOCKING]

323
00:27:08,219 --> 00:27:09,277
Dr. Hammond?

324
00:27:10,454 --> 00:27:11,887
Dr. Hector Hammond?

325
00:27:12,890 --> 00:27:15,051
We need to ask you to come with us.

326
00:27:17,895 --> 00:27:20,022
Did Adam put you up to this?

327
00:27:21,666 --> 00:27:23,156
[DOORS CLANK]

328
00:27:25,436 --> 00:27:27,495
[BELL RINGS]

329
00:27:27,672 --> 00:27:29,299
[WHIRRING THEN THUD]

330
00:27:29,473 --> 00:27:30,497
[BUZZER BUZZES]

331
00:27:30,675 --> 00:27:31,733
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

332
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:37,580
Get out of the car, please.

333
00:27:46,824 --> 00:27:48,689
[KEYPAD BEEPING]

334
00:27:58,836 --> 00:28:00,303
[BUZZER BUZZES]

335
00:28:01,706 --> 00:28:03,298
[BEEPS]

336
00:28:07,578 --> 00:28:08,977
[WHISPERS]
Whoa.

337
00:28:15,219 --> 00:28:17,050
[BEEPS]

338
00:28:24,428 --> 00:28:25,622
Dr. Hammond?

339
00:28:26,063 --> 00:28:27,223
Dr. Amanda Waller.

340
00:28:27,398 --> 00:28:32,097
I must apologize for the theatrics,
but the government does like its protocols.

341
00:28:32,270 --> 00:28:34,067
Please, follow me.

342
00:28:56,027 --> 00:28:58,222
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Is that what I think it is?

343
00:28:58,396 --> 00:29:01,024
An alien life form, doctor.

344
00:29:01,299 --> 00:29:03,631
The first that mankind
has ever encountered...

345
00:29:03,801 --> 00:29:07,237
...despite what the conspiracy theorists
would have you believe.

346
00:29:07,405 --> 00:29:11,102
We want you to do the initial assessment
of its physiology.

347
00:29:11,275 --> 00:29:13,140
My God.

348
00:29:16,213 --> 00:29:17,475
Why me?

349
00:29:17,648 --> 00:29:21,106
As a xenobiologist, your skills are
specifically suited to the task.

350
00:29:21,285 --> 00:29:22,343
Beyond that...

351
00:29:22,520 --> 00:29:24,283
...I'm not at liberty to tell you.

352
00:29:26,724 --> 00:29:28,316
Hello.

353
00:29:50,147 --> 00:29:51,375
[GRUNTS]

354
00:29:52,583 --> 00:29:53,675
[WHIMPERS]

355
00:29:59,623 --> 00:30:04,925
The eyes, nose, ears and mouth
are humanoid.

356
00:30:05,096 --> 00:30:09,362
In the left anterior thoracic region
is a 10-centimeter wound...

357
00:30:09,533 --> 00:30:13,162
...with jagged edges containing attached
cyanotic-colored coagulum.

358
00:30:14,005 --> 00:30:15,063
Okay, all right.

359
00:30:15,239 --> 00:30:17,901
Place the ring, then speak the oath.

360
00:30:20,578 --> 00:30:22,102
The oath.

361
00:30:22,380 --> 00:30:24,610
Because everybody knows the oath.

362
00:30:25,016 --> 00:30:27,450
Used to sing it in camp.

363
00:30:30,421 --> 00:30:34,118
I, Hal Jordan...

364
00:30:34,658 --> 00:30:36,888
...do solemnly swear...

365
00:30:37,061 --> 00:30:39,928
...to pledge allegiance...

366
00:30:40,464 --> 00:30:41,863
...to a lantern...

367
00:30:42,033 --> 00:30:45,867
...that I got from a dying purple alien...

368
00:30:46,470 --> 00:30:48,028
...in a swamp.

369
00:30:48,205 --> 00:30:50,105
HECTOR:
The epidermis is magenta.

370
00:30:50,274 --> 00:30:53,175
It appears transparent
and is extremely thin...

371
00:30:53,344 --> 00:30:58,577
...allowing visualization of muscles
and individual muscle fibers.

372
00:30:59,550 --> 00:31:02,747
"To infinity and beyond."

373
00:31:03,087 --> 00:31:05,612
"By the power of Grayskull."

374
00:31:05,790 --> 00:31:07,280
What the hell?!

375
00:31:07,458 --> 00:31:11,155
If you can fly me 100 miles in the middle
of nowhere, you'd think that you...

376
00:31:11,829 --> 00:31:13,296
No!

377
00:31:13,464 --> 00:31:16,456
[PANTING]

378
00:31:24,942 --> 00:31:29,242
In brightest day, in blackest night...

379
00:31:29,580 --> 00:31:32,549
...no evil shall escape my sight.

380
00:31:33,250 --> 00:31:36,185
Let those who worship evil's might...

381
00:31:37,788 --> 00:31:38,982
[GASPS]

382
00:31:41,092 --> 00:31:43,151
...beware my power:

383
00:31:44,128 --> 00:31:45,356
Green Lantern's light.

384
00:31:52,670 --> 00:31:55,662
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

385
00:31:57,441 --> 00:31:59,170
[KNOCKING CONTINUES]

386
00:32:05,049 --> 00:32:06,380
Carol.

387
00:32:06,951 --> 00:32:09,613
- Everything okay in there?
- It's fine.

388
00:32:10,387 --> 00:32:11,445
Well, can I come in?

389
00:32:11,622 --> 00:32:12,714
No.

390
00:32:12,890 --> 00:32:15,450
Yeah, no, because we're...
Uh, do you wanna get a drink?

391
00:32:16,393 --> 00:32:17,655
- Can we talk?
- Yeah.

392
00:32:17,995 --> 00:32:20,463
We can talk and drink.

393
00:32:31,542 --> 00:32:33,442
HECTOR: My initial analysis.
- Thank you, doctor.

394
00:32:33,611 --> 00:32:39,174
I don't need to tell you that the mere fact
that it's humanoid is extraordinary.

395
00:32:39,350 --> 00:32:44,344
It's indicating a convergent evolution,
or perhaps a common ancestry...

396
00:32:44,522 --> 00:32:47,889
...and the implications of that
are staggering.

397
00:32:48,058 --> 00:32:50,652
I mean, where did it come from?

398
00:32:50,828 --> 00:32:54,059
This could completely change the way
that the world views itself.

399
00:32:54,231 --> 00:32:57,325
You imagine the way that the public
will react to this?

400
00:32:58,068 --> 00:33:01,162
Um, but I know that
that won't happen. I do.

401
00:33:01,338 --> 00:33:04,330
Like yourself, doctor,
I'm a seeker of truth.

402
00:33:04,508 --> 00:33:07,033
But the people who pay for facilities
like this...

403
00:33:07,244 --> 00:33:09,940
...have other priorities
and the power to enforce them.

404
00:33:10,114 --> 00:33:11,945
So I keep it a secret.

405
00:33:12,116 --> 00:33:14,778
People like us have to work
within the system, doctor.

406
00:33:14,952 --> 00:33:17,546
We do the best we can.

407
00:33:19,690 --> 00:33:20,952
Right.

408
00:33:21,225 --> 00:33:23,489
[SAM COOKE'S "THAT'S WHERE IT'S AT"
PLAYING ON JUKEBOX]

409
00:33:23,661 --> 00:33:25,322
WOMAN:
Pick that up.

410
00:33:27,998 --> 00:33:29,625
I, um...

411
00:33:30,434 --> 00:33:31,696
I'm really sorry.

412
00:33:32,469 --> 00:33:34,494
Did you just apologize?

413
00:33:35,105 --> 00:33:38,370
You haven't been replaced by an alien
or something?

414
00:33:39,076 --> 00:33:40,202
No.

415
00:33:40,811 --> 00:33:41,869
I'm good.

416
00:33:42,613 --> 00:33:44,604
Ah. I'm good.

417
00:33:44,982 --> 00:33:47,644
I'm good, totally good. Uh...

418
00:33:49,753 --> 00:33:50,811
[SIGHS]

419
00:33:50,988 --> 00:33:52,285
Do you think I'm irresponsible?

420
00:33:52,456 --> 00:33:55,448
[LAUGHING]

421
00:33:56,594 --> 00:33:59,586
No need to answer. That's fine.

422
00:34:00,497 --> 00:34:02,021
Hal. Ha, ha.

423
00:34:06,704 --> 00:34:08,433
You look pretty.

424
00:34:11,508 --> 00:34:15,171
And we haven't been in this place
together since...

425
00:34:16,180 --> 00:34:17,272
...that night.

426
00:34:18,315 --> 00:34:21,011
- You forgot it was my birthday.
HAL: Did I?

427
00:34:21,185 --> 00:34:22,482
Mm.

428
00:34:22,653 --> 00:34:26,316
That was also the night...
The first time that we ever...

429
00:34:27,825 --> 00:34:29,452
...flew together.

430
00:34:32,196 --> 00:34:35,427
You've been flying ever since
with anyone who'd get in the plane.

431
00:34:36,100 --> 00:34:39,092
[THE FLEETWOODS' "COME SOFTLY TO ME"
PLAYING ON JUKEBOX]

432
00:34:40,971 --> 00:34:44,031
Oh, yeah.

433
00:34:44,475 --> 00:34:45,874
- Oh, no.
HAL: Come on.

434
00:34:46,043 --> 00:34:47,510
- No, yeah, let's go.
CAROL: Mm-mm.

435
00:34:47,678 --> 00:34:50,203
HAL: Dance with me.
- No.

436
00:34:51,015 --> 00:34:53,506
[HAL SINGING "COME SOFTLY TO ME"]

437
00:34:53,684 --> 00:34:54,912
No.

438
00:34:57,454 --> 00:34:58,785
No.

439
00:34:59,390 --> 00:35:00,857
Hal. No.

440
00:35:01,025 --> 00:35:04,290
[HAL CONTINUES SINGING
"COME SOFTLY TO ME"]

441
00:35:04,461 --> 00:35:05,485
No.

442
00:35:06,797 --> 00:35:09,789
[CAROL CHUCKLING]

443
00:35:11,001 --> 00:35:12,866
I really am sorry.

444
00:35:13,037 --> 00:35:16,939
Oh. It's okay.
The contract isn't quite dead yet.

445
00:35:17,107 --> 00:35:18,506
I told you I was good at this.

446
00:35:18,676 --> 00:35:21,201
I wasn't talking about the contract.

447
00:35:24,515 --> 00:35:28,815
I would've screwed this up. You know?

448
00:35:29,653 --> 00:35:32,019
Even if I didn't go to the Air Force...

449
00:35:33,023 --> 00:35:35,355
...I would've found some way to...

450
00:35:36,360 --> 00:35:39,158
- You and me, I would've blown it.
- Yeah, is that what you tell yourself?

451
00:35:39,330 --> 00:35:41,525
Mm. What do you tell yourself?

452
00:35:45,169 --> 00:35:47,865
That you were scared
I was getting too close.

453
00:35:51,408 --> 00:35:54,002
You know what I spent
my afternoon doing?

454
00:35:54,178 --> 00:35:55,645
What?

455
00:35:55,979 --> 00:35:57,970
Worrying about you.

456
00:35:59,583 --> 00:36:04,384
I went over every inch of the flight data.
There was nothing wrong with the plane.

457
00:36:05,222 --> 00:36:08,055
- What happened up there?
HAL: Thanks for the dance.

458
00:36:22,806 --> 00:36:24,205
[KEYS JINGLING]

459
00:36:25,776 --> 00:36:28,768
[ALL GRUNTING]

460
00:36:36,954 --> 00:36:38,615
BOB:
I told you to watch your back.

461
00:36:39,056 --> 00:36:42,082
You cost us all our jobs,
you son of a bitch.

462
00:37:01,512 --> 00:37:03,002
Pathetic.

463
00:37:03,447 --> 00:37:06,974
Bastard's been living off his old man's
reputation his whole life.

464
00:37:13,056 --> 00:37:14,523
Hey.

465
00:37:15,426 --> 00:37:16,916
Hey!

466
00:37:18,195 --> 00:37:20,095
My face is just getting warmed up.

467
00:37:26,170 --> 00:37:29,162
[CAR ALARMS BLARING]

468
00:37:40,551 --> 00:37:41,643
[YELLS]

469
00:37:43,420 --> 00:37:46,412
[GRUNTING]

470
00:38:03,474 --> 00:38:06,910
[YELLING]

471
00:38:08,979 --> 00:38:11,106
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

472
00:38:11,281 --> 00:38:12,305
[SCREAMS]

473
00:38:12,483 --> 00:38:13,973
[PANTING]

474
00:38:14,518 --> 00:38:16,281
[SCREAMS]

475
00:38:16,854 --> 00:38:19,846
[GRUNTING]

476
00:38:25,028 --> 00:38:26,154
[SCREAMS]

477
00:38:56,727 --> 00:38:57,819
[GRUNTS]

478
00:39:58,488 --> 00:40:01,184
[GRUNTING]

479
00:40:01,358 --> 00:40:03,883
[SCREAMING]

480
00:40:09,333 --> 00:40:12,325
[GRUNTING]

481
00:40:41,131 --> 00:40:42,223
[GASPS]

482
00:41:09,393 --> 00:41:11,361
[WHISPERS]
Whoa.

483
00:41:17,567 --> 00:41:19,592
[GRUNTING]

484
00:41:21,004 --> 00:41:23,495
[WHISTLING]

485
00:41:23,674 --> 00:41:24,902
[GRUNTS]

486
00:41:28,912 --> 00:41:31,346
Have you concluded admiring yourself?

487
00:41:31,515 --> 00:41:33,005
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Uh...

488
00:41:33,183 --> 00:41:34,343
Yeah.

489
00:41:34,518 --> 00:41:38,318
Well, your ring translator
is functioning properly.

490
00:41:38,522 --> 00:41:41,685
Your mask will appear when protection
of your identity is required.

491
00:41:41,858 --> 00:41:43,553
There is no need for it on Oa.

492
00:41:43,994 --> 00:41:45,621
A talking fish.

493
00:41:45,796 --> 00:41:47,457
Actually, my race is Xudarian.

494
00:41:47,631 --> 00:41:51,123
Our DNA does somewhat resemble
your own ichthyological species.

495
00:41:51,968 --> 00:41:55,529
I am Tomar-Re, protector of Sector 2813
and home to...

496
00:41:55,706 --> 00:42:00,200
80,012 galaxies,
2.34 million sentient species.

497
00:42:01,078 --> 00:42:02,170
How do I know that?

498
00:42:02,345 --> 00:42:03,972
The induction process.

499
00:42:04,147 --> 00:42:08,584
It activates the ring's higher functions,
including a working knowledge base.

500
00:42:08,752 --> 00:42:09,980
In truth, we were curious.

501
00:42:10,153 --> 00:42:14,647
The process had never been attempted on
a species as young as humans before.

502
00:42:16,760 --> 00:42:21,788
As you are the first to be chosen,
I've been sent to welcome you here.

503
00:42:23,100 --> 00:42:25,534
And here is?

504
00:42:29,339 --> 00:42:31,569
TOMAR-RE:
Welcome to Oa.

505
00:42:35,946 --> 00:42:39,473
This planet has been our home
for countless millennia.

506
00:42:39,649 --> 00:42:42,675
It was created for us by the Guardians.

507
00:42:42,853 --> 00:42:44,514
Guardians?

508
00:42:44,688 --> 00:42:46,451
There stands their Citadel.

509
00:42:47,090 --> 00:42:50,253
They are immortals,
among the most ancient of races.

510
00:42:50,427 --> 00:42:54,659
They made all you see
and are responsible for all we are and do.

511
00:42:55,432 --> 00:42:57,832
Since time immemorial,
the Green Lantern Corps...

512
00:42:58,001 --> 00:43:02,836
...has served as the keepers of peace,
order and justice throughout the universe.

513
00:43:03,273 --> 00:43:07,107
To be chosen to join its ranks
is the highest of honors...

514
00:43:07,277 --> 00:43:09,609
...and the greatest of responsibilities.

515
00:43:09,780 --> 00:43:12,271
Yeah. Yeah, that part I heard about.

516
00:43:12,983 --> 00:43:14,280
We're going to fly now.

517
00:43:16,520 --> 00:43:18,647
- Fly?
- Absolutely.

518
00:43:19,790 --> 00:43:21,451
All right.

519
00:43:22,159 --> 00:43:24,184
I can do that.

520
00:43:29,199 --> 00:43:30,666
Join me.

521
00:43:32,335 --> 00:43:34,200
I can do that.

522
00:43:41,578 --> 00:43:44,138
[HAL YELLING]

523
00:43:44,314 --> 00:43:46,145
[HAL LAUGHING]

524
00:43:46,316 --> 00:43:47,977
Yeah!

525
00:43:48,652 --> 00:43:50,051
Whoa!

526
00:43:50,854 --> 00:43:52,287
Whoa!

527
00:43:55,992 --> 00:43:58,153
[HAL CHUCKLING]

528
00:44:23,386 --> 00:44:24,819
What is that?

529
00:44:24,988 --> 00:44:27,889
TOMAR-RE: It's the energy
that's generated from the Central Battery.

530
00:44:28,058 --> 00:44:31,550
Its power comes from the will
of every living creature in the universe.

531
00:44:31,995 --> 00:44:36,932
It, in turn, charges your lantern,
which, in turn, charges your ring.

532
00:44:37,100 --> 00:44:40,536
Even your suit is comprised
entirely of energy.

533
00:44:40,971 --> 00:44:42,268
What's with all the green?

534
00:44:42,439 --> 00:44:43,906
Green is the color of will.

535
00:44:44,074 --> 00:44:45,632
The Guardians harnessed will...

536
00:44:45,809 --> 00:44:49,074
...because it's the strongest
source of energy in the universe.

537
00:44:53,283 --> 00:44:54,978
HAL:
There's so many.

538
00:44:55,151 --> 00:44:58,746
TOMAR-RE: The stars you can see from
your home planet on the clearest night...

539
00:44:58,922 --> 00:45:00,981
...your sector is a thousand times larger.

540
00:45:02,359 --> 00:45:07,262
And 3600 Lanterns,
each with a sector just as vast.

541
00:45:07,430 --> 00:45:10,422
[ALL CHATTERING
IN ALIEN LANGUAGES]

542
00:45:31,254 --> 00:45:34,621
Lanterns, I've called you here
to this unprecedented gathering...

543
00:45:34,791 --> 00:45:38,090
...because we face
an unprecedented danger.

544
00:45:39,729 --> 00:45:44,098
Our four Lantern brothers
were killed by an enemy called Parallax.

545
00:45:45,268 --> 00:45:48,704
An enemy we don't yet fully understand.

546
00:45:49,139 --> 00:45:53,803
We do know it's powerful enough
to destroy entire civilizations.

547
00:45:55,178 --> 00:45:59,137
Powerful enough
to defeat even Abin Sur...

548
00:45:59,616 --> 00:46:01,743
...our finest warrior...

549
00:46:03,186 --> 00:46:05,313
...whose light can never be replaced.

550
00:46:05,488 --> 00:46:07,956
[ALL MURMURING
IN ALIEN LANGUAGES]

551
00:46:10,727 --> 00:46:14,128
SINESTRO: The Guardians have charged me
to lead a squadron of Lanterns...

552
00:46:14,297 --> 00:46:16,026
...in an assault on Parallax.

553
00:46:16,199 --> 00:46:19,930
We will seek out and find this enemy.

554
00:46:21,338 --> 00:46:23,568
And we will destroy it.

555
00:46:24,240 --> 00:46:28,040
Alone, we are now vulnerable.

556
00:46:28,311 --> 00:46:31,803
United, we are still invincible.

557
00:46:32,549 --> 00:46:34,380
We have never been defeated.

558
00:46:34,818 --> 00:46:36,683
Will we be defeated now?

559
00:46:36,853 --> 00:46:38,013
ALL:
No!

560
00:46:38,989 --> 00:46:43,517
SINESTRO: It was for this moment
that we were created.

561
00:46:43,693 --> 00:46:46,821
But I don't need to tell you your duty.

562
00:46:46,997 --> 00:46:49,989
I don't need to tell you who we are.

563
00:46:50,166 --> 00:46:52,657
[GUARDIAN SHOUTING
IN ALIEN LANGUAGE]

564
00:46:53,603 --> 00:46:57,403
<i>LANTERNS [CHANTING]:
We are the Corps! We are the Corps!</i>

565
00:46:58,341 --> 00:47:02,710
<i>We are the Corps! We are the Corps!</i>

566
00:47:06,483 --> 00:47:09,941
TOMAR-RE:
Your will turns thought into reality.

567
00:47:10,453 --> 00:47:13,115
To master the ring,
you must learn to focus your will...

568
00:47:13,289 --> 00:47:16,315
...and create what you see in your mind.

569
00:47:19,629 --> 00:47:22,189
The ring's limits
are only what you can imagine.

570
00:47:27,537 --> 00:47:28,868
Do that again.

571
00:47:29,039 --> 00:47:30,301
Now you try.

572
00:47:32,542 --> 00:47:33,702
Concentrate.

573
00:47:36,946 --> 00:47:37,970
[BLOWS]

574
00:47:48,825 --> 00:47:49,917
[RING BEEPING]

575
00:47:50,093 --> 00:47:53,290
The ring will inform you
where there is an imminent threat.

576
00:47:53,963 --> 00:47:56,557
[GRUNTING]

577
00:47:56,733 --> 00:47:59,566
TOMAR-RE:
This particular threat's name is Kilowog.

578
00:47:59,736 --> 00:48:02,227
He'll be your combat training officer.

579
00:48:02,572 --> 00:48:06,133
<i>HAL: Whoa!
- Never let your guard down, poozer.</i>

580
00:48:07,010 --> 00:48:09,171
Welcome to Ring Slinging 101.

581
00:48:09,345 --> 00:48:10,903
Or as I like to call it:

582
00:48:11,081 --> 00:48:13,948
The worst day of your worthless life.

583
00:48:16,486 --> 00:48:19,455
The human. Ain't never seen one before.

584
00:48:19,622 --> 00:48:21,886
[KILOWOG SNIFFS THEN SNORTS]

585
00:48:22,058 --> 00:48:23,992
- You smell funny.
- Ugh.

586
00:48:24,527 --> 00:48:25,551
I smell funny?

587
00:48:25,728 --> 00:48:29,494
Yeah, I heard about humans.
Think you're the center of the universe.

588
00:48:29,766 --> 00:48:33,293
You want to be a Lantern?
You gotta commit to the Corps.

589
00:48:35,972 --> 00:48:38,440
<i>All right, poozer.
Let's see what you've got.</i>

590
00:48:41,911 --> 00:48:44,311
[GRUNTING]

591
00:48:51,721 --> 00:48:55,179
Your constructs are only gonna be
as strong as your will.

592
00:48:55,358 --> 00:48:56,882
And your will is pathetic.

593
00:49:01,731 --> 00:49:03,926
I'm gonna work you
and I'm gonna hit you...

594
00:49:04,100 --> 00:49:07,536
...until your will is strong enough
to be worthy of the Corps.

595
00:49:07,704 --> 00:49:11,231
[BOTH GRUNTING]

596
00:49:20,550 --> 00:49:21,915
KILOWOG:
Next lesson.

597
00:49:24,921 --> 00:49:27,048
Ha, ha. Feel that?

598
00:49:27,223 --> 00:49:29,851
It's the gravitational pull
of your average sun.

599
00:49:30,026 --> 00:49:33,484
Makes flying through space
very dangerous.

600
00:49:33,663 --> 00:49:36,826
The bigger you are,
the quicker you burn.

601
00:49:39,369 --> 00:49:41,394
Gravity's a bitch.

602
00:49:44,174 --> 00:49:46,369
Here, let me help you.

603
00:49:49,078 --> 00:49:53,947
Remember, your enemy,
he's not gonna play fair.

604
00:50:00,423 --> 00:50:03,392
Well, that's good advice.
Thanks, gorgeous.

605
00:50:03,560 --> 00:50:05,027
SINESTRO:
So...

606
00:50:06,563 --> 00:50:08,360
...this is the human.

607
00:50:09,132 --> 00:50:11,600
When I learned Abin Sur's ring
had chosen you...

608
00:50:11,768 --> 00:50:13,292
...I said there had to be a mistake.

609
00:50:13,469 --> 00:50:15,767
[KILOWOG GROANING]

610
00:50:15,939 --> 00:50:18,407
I see nothing to change my mind.

611
00:50:19,042 --> 00:50:20,737
I'll take it from here, Kilowog.

612
00:50:22,912 --> 00:50:25,107
The Corps is only as strong
as its weakest link.

613
00:50:25,782 --> 00:50:28,376
And I will tolerate no weak links.

614
00:50:28,885 --> 00:50:30,250
You understand me?

615
00:50:32,088 --> 00:50:34,750
Are you afraid, human?

616
00:50:37,493 --> 00:50:38,721
Are you afraid?

617
00:50:38,895 --> 00:50:39,919
Don't.

618
00:50:40,096 --> 00:50:41,188
[CHUCKLES]

619
00:50:42,065 --> 00:50:43,760
Don't do that.

620
00:50:48,204 --> 00:50:49,501
Shall we?

621
00:50:52,308 --> 00:50:53,639
Sure.

622
00:50:54,711 --> 00:50:56,406
A sword?

623
00:50:56,579 --> 00:50:58,410
How human.

624
00:50:59,115 --> 00:51:02,107
[BOTH GRUNTING]

625
00:51:08,491 --> 00:51:11,051
I do believe I smell fear.

626
00:51:12,528 --> 00:51:13,893
[YELLS]

627
00:51:14,964 --> 00:51:16,090
[PANTING]

628
00:51:16,266 --> 00:51:18,200
I'm a Green Lantern.

629
00:51:20,270 --> 00:51:22,261
I fear nothing.

630
00:51:24,374 --> 00:51:26,433
Fear is the enemy of will.

631
00:51:26,609 --> 00:51:28,440
Will is what makes you take action.

632
00:51:31,981 --> 00:51:35,610
Fear is what stops you
and makes you weak.

633
00:51:41,457 --> 00:51:43,448
Makes your constructs feeble.

634
00:51:53,736 --> 00:51:56,796
You must ignore your fear.
When you're afraid, you can't act.

635
00:51:56,973 --> 00:52:00,500
When you can't act, you can't defend.
If you can't defend, you die.

636
00:52:05,581 --> 00:52:07,572
You reek of fear, Hal Jordan.

637
00:52:08,151 --> 00:52:09,812
Abin Sur was a great warrior.

638
00:52:10,286 --> 00:52:12,049
My mentor.

639
00:52:12,355 --> 00:52:13,947
My friend.

640
00:52:14,524 --> 00:52:18,620
You insult his memory
by wearing his ring.

641
00:52:36,412 --> 00:52:40,041
I'm done. He's right. I'm only human.
We're not ready to defend the universe.

642
00:52:40,216 --> 00:52:43,276
A few days ago, we thought we were
the only ones in the universe.

643
00:52:43,453 --> 00:52:47,116
The ring chose you. It wouldn't have
if it hadn't seen something in you.

644
00:52:47,290 --> 00:52:48,314
Oh, yeah?

645
00:52:48,491 --> 00:52:50,686
Something you yourself don't yet see.

646
00:52:50,860 --> 00:52:52,794
The ring never makes a mistake.

647
00:52:53,896 --> 00:52:55,454
This time it did.

648
00:53:19,555 --> 00:53:20,749
[SIGHS]

649
00:53:43,613 --> 00:53:45,945
HECTOR:
- That until recently, we didn't realize...

650
00:53:46,115 --> 00:53:50,984
...that many of these little critters that we've
been calling bacteria weren't bacteria at all.

651
00:53:51,154 --> 00:53:56,023
They were an entirely different type
of primitive prokaryotic cell.

652
00:53:56,192 --> 00:54:00,128
These little buggers, called archaeans,
are still poorly understood.

653
00:54:00,296 --> 00:54:02,389
[STUDENTS THINKING INDISTINCTLY]

654
00:54:02,899 --> 00:54:04,059
Um...

655
00:54:04,233 --> 00:54:07,259
But might turn out to be
different from bacteria...

656
00:54:07,437 --> 00:54:10,429
[STUDENTS THINKING INDISTINCTLY]

657
00:54:10,606 --> 00:54:14,804
But might turn out to be as different
from bacteria as bacteria is from us.

658
00:54:14,977 --> 00:54:16,171
Some call them extremophiles...

659
00:54:16,345 --> 00:54:17,505
[MICHAEL YAWNS]

660
00:54:17,680 --> 00:54:21,138
...because they live in the most extreme
environments on Earth, such as...

661
00:54:21,317 --> 00:54:23,444
<i>MICHAEL [THINKING]:
God, he's so boring.</i>

662
00:54:23,619 --> 00:54:25,280
...the boiling waters of a geyser.

663
00:54:25,455 --> 00:54:26,888
<i>MICHAEL [THINKING]:
What a loser.</i>

664
00:54:27,890 --> 00:54:29,653
- Michael!
- Huh?

665
00:54:30,626 --> 00:54:31,650
What did you say?

666
00:54:32,528 --> 00:54:33,722
I didn't say anything.

667
00:54:36,866 --> 00:54:38,458
Did you just call me a loser?

668
00:54:38,634 --> 00:54:40,727
<i>MICHAEL [THINKING]:
What kind of freak is this guy?</i>

669
00:54:40,903 --> 00:54:42,495
"Freak"?!

670
00:54:43,406 --> 00:54:44,668
[SCOFFS]

671
00:54:48,077 --> 00:54:50,045
[MICHAEL YELLS THEN GRUNTS]

672
00:54:50,213 --> 00:54:51,612
[STUDENTS GASPING AND SCREAMING]

673
00:54:51,781 --> 00:54:54,750
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

674
00:55:01,090 --> 00:55:02,751
Class dismissed.

675
00:55:28,317 --> 00:55:30,182
[CELL PHONE BEEPING]

676
00:55:45,101 --> 00:55:46,966
So how you been?

677
00:55:47,370 --> 00:55:49,133
Been a while.

678
00:55:50,373 --> 00:55:53,433
So you had a rough night last night.
Did you get her name, huh?

679
00:55:53,609 --> 00:55:56,339
[BOTH LAUGHING]

680
00:55:56,512 --> 00:55:59,003
You need to get some sleep, son.

681
00:55:59,549 --> 00:56:02,541
- Have a seat.
- What can I do for you, Dad?

682
00:56:02,718 --> 00:56:05,152
Well, actually, you've already done it.

683
00:56:05,721 --> 00:56:07,484
For me and for your country.

684
00:56:07,990 --> 00:56:09,480
What are you talking about?

685
00:56:09,659 --> 00:56:14,824
I'm talking about you impressing
a whole lot of very important people.

686
00:56:17,133 --> 00:56:18,760
Where did you get that?

687
00:56:18,935 --> 00:56:22,462
I'm on a subcommittee
overseeing the agencies involved.

688
00:56:22,638 --> 00:56:27,632
- Top-secret, of course.
- It was you. That's why they chose me.

689
00:56:27,977 --> 00:56:31,913
Because of this, we're gonna be able
to get you a top post on the inside now...

690
00:56:32,081 --> 00:56:33,742
...helping to oversee the operation.

691
00:56:33,916 --> 00:56:38,512
There are scientists
that worked their whole lives for this.

692
00:56:38,688 --> 00:56:40,656
- Mm-hm.
- People more qualified.

693
00:56:40,823 --> 00:56:42,120
And less connected.

694
00:56:42,291 --> 00:56:45,920
Don't be naive, son.
It's the way the world works.

695
00:56:46,228 --> 00:56:49,595
You have to seize an opportunity
when it presents itself.

696
00:56:52,335 --> 00:56:54,132
<i>HAMMOND [THINKING]:
He'll never get it.</i>

697
00:56:54,303 --> 00:56:55,361
<i>Just wasting his life away.</i>

698
00:56:55,538 --> 00:56:56,562
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

699
00:56:56,739 --> 00:56:58,206
<i>What an embarrassment.</i>

700
00:57:00,009 --> 00:57:03,342
Bill! Ha. How are you?

701
00:57:03,512 --> 00:57:05,173
I'm terrific.

702
00:57:05,348 --> 00:57:09,284
No, no, no. Just finishing up a meeting.
Got plenty of time.

703
00:57:32,404 --> 00:57:34,395
[GROWLS]

704
00:57:39,845 --> 00:57:42,837
[GRUNTING]

705
00:57:46,384 --> 00:57:49,376
[ROARING]

706
00:57:59,798 --> 00:58:01,993
[GRUNTING]

707
00:58:03,702 --> 00:58:06,899
[BOTH SCREAMING]

708
00:58:08,607 --> 00:58:12,839
<i>SINESTRO: With my own eyes I saw this
creature induce fear in our finest warriors...</i>

709
00:58:13,011 --> 00:58:15,138
...and then feed on that fear.

710
00:58:15,914 --> 00:58:17,347
There's more.

711
00:58:17,515 --> 00:58:21,508
We've tracked its trajectory.
Parallax is headed for Oa.

712
00:58:22,020 --> 00:58:24,352
Never before has an enemy
dared attack us here.

713
00:58:24,522 --> 00:58:26,786
You must tell me what you know.

714
00:58:29,261 --> 00:58:31,695
FIRST GUARDIAN:
Will has always been our sole weapon...

715
00:58:31,863 --> 00:58:34,559
...against the forces of darkness
in the universe.

716
00:58:35,066 --> 00:58:38,627
But as that power began to seem
insufficient...

717
00:58:38,803 --> 00:58:41,271
...a great debate arose among us.

718
00:58:41,439 --> 00:58:43,873
Should we exploit
another source of power...

719
00:58:44,209 --> 00:58:48,202
...one we had long since sworn
should never be used?

720
00:58:48,813 --> 00:58:50,303
Fear.

721
00:58:50,482 --> 00:58:54,111
But the power of fear
was too unpredictable.

722
00:58:54,286 --> 00:58:56,948
The chance of corruption too great.

723
00:58:57,122 --> 00:58:59,556
And so we decided against it.

724
00:58:59,724 --> 00:59:03,717
<i>All of us, that is, except one.</i>

725
00:59:04,429 --> 00:59:08,195
<i>Alone, this Guardian
entered the forbidden chamber.</i>

726
00:59:08,366 --> 00:59:12,325
<i>He wanted to prove the light of fear
could be mastered.</i>

727
00:59:12,504 --> 00:59:15,337
<i>His intentions were pure...</i>

728
00:59:15,507 --> 00:59:18,567
<i>... but his hopes were naive.</i>

729
00:59:19,411 --> 00:59:22,278
<i>Consumed by the yellow power of fear...</i>

730
00:59:22,447 --> 00:59:27,009
<i>... the Guardian became the very evil
he had wished to destroy.</i>

731
00:59:27,185 --> 00:59:29,244
<i>He became Parallax.</i>

732
00:59:36,861 --> 00:59:39,762
For the universe's safety and his own...

733
00:59:39,931 --> 00:59:44,163
...Abin Sur was charged with
imprisoning Parallax in the Lost Sector.

734
00:59:44,336 --> 00:59:45,735
But he escaped.

735
00:59:45,904 --> 00:59:49,840
Feeding on the fear of others,
he grew larger, more powerful.

736
00:59:50,008 --> 00:59:51,202
And is now headed here...

737
00:59:51,376 --> 00:59:54,675
...to take his revenge on you
and destroy the Corps.

738
01:00:01,553 --> 01:00:03,714
Then we have no choice.

739
01:00:04,356 --> 01:00:08,122
We must prepare to harness the power
of our enemy and fight fear with fear.

740
01:00:08,293 --> 01:00:11,456
To protect our sectors,
we must be able to defend ourselves.

741
01:00:12,664 --> 01:00:15,428
We must forge a yellow ring.

742
01:00:24,209 --> 01:00:25,233
CREWMAN:
Watch your step.

743
01:00:25,410 --> 01:00:27,037
MAN: Senator.
WOMAN: Senator.

744
01:00:27,212 --> 01:00:30,147
<i>[SINGING]
Don't have to worry about me no more</i>

745
01:00:30,315 --> 01:00:33,512
<i>I'm gone</i>

746
01:00:34,285 --> 01:00:38,312
<i>I'm gone, I'm gone</i>

747
01:00:40,859 --> 01:00:41,917
TOM:
Hello.

748
01:00:42,093 --> 01:00:43,321
Hi.

749
01:00:43,495 --> 01:00:46,487
[BAND PLAYING "BAREFOOTIN"']

750
01:00:48,233 --> 01:00:50,861
<i>SINGER [SINGING]:
Everybody get on your feet</i>

751
01:00:52,103 --> 01:00:54,333
<i>You make me nervous
When you're in your seat</i>

752
01:00:55,507 --> 01:00:56,997
Rough night, huh?

753
01:00:58,410 --> 01:00:59,672
Hector.

754
01:01:00,745 --> 01:01:02,610
How you doing?
What have you been up to?

755
01:01:02,781 --> 01:01:05,375
- Same old, same old.
- Yeah. Me too.

756
01:01:05,550 --> 01:01:10,419
Hal Jordan. Worst pilot I've ever seen.
Or the best. Not quite sure.

757
01:01:10,588 --> 01:01:11,748
I've been called both.

758
01:01:11,923 --> 01:01:15,415
- Glad you could make it, son.
- I was a little surprised I got the invite.

759
01:01:15,593 --> 01:01:16,753
No, you're family, Hal.

760
01:01:16,928 --> 01:01:19,658
There are thinkers in this world
and there are doers.

761
01:01:19,831 --> 01:01:21,594
And you are one of the doers.

762
01:01:23,401 --> 01:01:25,892
Yeah, but the thinkers
make what I do possible.

763
01:01:26,071 --> 01:01:28,437
Wouldn't have a plane
unless someone thought it up.

764
01:01:28,606 --> 01:01:30,005
Of course.

765
01:01:30,208 --> 01:01:32,142
Excuse me, I need a drink.

766
01:01:33,812 --> 01:01:36,645
- I gotta get back to work. This is work.
- Yes, sir.

767
01:01:36,815 --> 01:01:39,477
- Nice to see you, son.
HAL: You too. You too.

768
01:01:46,091 --> 01:01:47,922
Nice.

769
01:01:48,460 --> 01:01:49,654
[CAROL CLEARS THROAT]

770
01:01:49,828 --> 01:01:52,695
Yeah, my dad used to train in it.

771
01:01:53,631 --> 01:01:56,395
I was talking about your dress.

772
01:01:58,803 --> 01:02:00,600
Nice jacket.

773
01:02:00,772 --> 01:02:02,933
Last time I checked,
you didn't even own one.

774
01:02:03,108 --> 01:02:05,804
Yeah, I've been shaking up
the wardrobe lately.

775
01:02:05,977 --> 01:02:09,504
Congratulations on the contract.
How'd you manage to pull that off?

776
01:02:09,681 --> 01:02:13,014
I pointed out you only won because you
broke the rules of engagement.

777
01:02:13,218 --> 01:02:16,346
And Tom figured out
how to give the Sabres more altitude.

778
01:02:16,521 --> 01:02:19,786
So I guess in a way,
without even meaning to...

779
01:02:19,958 --> 01:02:21,653
...you actually did us a favor.

780
01:02:23,461 --> 01:02:24,860
Look...

781
01:02:25,997 --> 01:02:28,056
...I'm uncomfortable
with the word "hero."

782
01:02:28,233 --> 01:02:29,825
<i>SINGER [SINGING]:
Hey</i>

783
01:02:30,001 --> 01:02:31,025
[CAROL LAUGHS]

784
01:02:31,202 --> 01:02:34,194
[CROWD CHEERING AND APPLAUDING]

785
01:02:36,741 --> 01:02:39,039
CARL:
Thank you. Thank you all for joining us.

786
01:02:39,210 --> 01:02:40,370
Great evening.

787
01:02:40,545 --> 01:02:44,777
Somebody very special I'd like to thank
for helping us to nail this contract:

788
01:02:45,483 --> 01:02:47,849
My daughter, Carol Ferris.

789
01:02:48,019 --> 01:02:49,043
Come on!

790
01:02:49,220 --> 01:02:51,780
[CROWD CHEERING AND APPLAUDING]

791
01:02:58,796 --> 01:03:00,593
Congratulations, Carol.

792
01:03:00,765 --> 01:03:02,824
I take one look at you, young lady...

793
01:03:03,001 --> 01:03:05,401
...or at Hal Jordan over there,
spitting image of his dad...

794
01:03:05,570 --> 01:03:07,538
MAN 1: Whoo!
- You give us hope.

795
01:03:07,972 --> 01:03:09,735
A toast to our future.

796
01:03:09,908 --> 01:03:11,705
MAN 2: Hear, hear!
MAN 3: To the future!

797
01:03:11,876 --> 01:03:12,968
HAMMOND:
We're in good hands.

798
01:03:13,144 --> 01:03:15,305
[CROWD CHEERING AND APPLAUDING]

799
01:03:19,984 --> 01:03:22,976
[GROOVE ARMADA'S
"HANDS OF TIME" PLAYING]

800
01:03:29,460 --> 01:03:32,258
Hector! Oh, my God! Hey!

801
01:03:37,535 --> 01:03:40,060
- Congratulations. Um...
CAROL: Thank you.

802
01:03:40,238 --> 01:03:43,833
Here's to you and Hal, the future.

803
01:03:44,576 --> 01:03:47,875
Yeah, heh, I'm sorry.

804
01:03:48,313 --> 01:03:52,010
I know it couldn't have been easy
growing up with your dad.

805
01:03:52,183 --> 01:03:55,175
But, hey, you're doing great, so... Ha, ha.

806
01:03:55,353 --> 01:03:57,116
I am. I'm doing great. Ha, ha.

807
01:03:57,288 --> 01:03:59,950
- He's right, though. I'm not a doer.
CAROL: Ha, ha.

808
01:04:00,124 --> 01:04:02,786
Although I did get to examine
an alien body recently.

809
01:04:02,961 --> 01:04:04,485
That was very cool.

810
01:04:04,662 --> 01:04:08,223
I can't tell anyone about it,
but, hey, you can't have everything.

811
01:04:08,399 --> 01:04:10,663
Hector telling you another
of his science-fiction stories?

812
01:04:10,835 --> 01:04:12,826
<i>HAMMOND [THINKING]:
What the hell's wrong with him?</i>

813
01:04:13,004 --> 01:04:14,767
<i>Can't keep his mouth shut.</i>

814
01:04:15,373 --> 01:04:17,773
You really do have
a creative imagination.

815
01:04:17,942 --> 01:04:19,273
Bye.

816
01:04:19,577 --> 01:04:20,601
ASSISTANT:
Senator.

817
01:04:21,145 --> 01:04:23,807
I apologize. We really must go.

818
01:04:24,782 --> 01:04:26,875
- Good night, Carol.
- Good night.

819
01:04:30,588 --> 01:04:31,612
MAN 4:
Senator!

820
01:04:31,889 --> 01:04:33,356
Hey.

821
01:04:34,192 --> 01:04:35,284
MAN 5:
Thanks for everything.

822
01:04:45,803 --> 01:04:47,600
WOMAN 1:
Bye, senator!

823
01:05:00,818 --> 01:05:02,115
[ALARM BLARING]

824
01:05:13,464 --> 01:05:16,865
Get the crash crew here.
Our helicopter's going down.

825
01:05:19,470 --> 01:05:20,767
[BEEPING]

826
01:05:23,374 --> 01:05:24,966
[ALL GRUNTING]

827
01:05:27,145 --> 01:05:28,271
Oh, my God.

828
01:05:30,181 --> 01:05:33,150
[CROWD SCREAMING]

829
01:05:51,169 --> 01:05:52,431
[GASPING]

830
01:05:59,844 --> 01:06:01,175
[CROWD SCREAMING]

831
01:06:01,346 --> 01:06:02,472
[SCREAMS]

832
01:06:17,962 --> 01:06:18,986
[ENGINE STOPS]

833
01:06:21,499 --> 01:06:24,491
[CROWD MURMURING]

834
01:06:29,674 --> 01:06:31,904
[CROWD SCREAMING]

835
01:06:36,381 --> 01:06:38,849
WOMAN 2:
What is that? What is that?

836
01:07:01,038 --> 01:07:03,563
[CARL CRYING]

837
01:07:21,292 --> 01:07:24,284
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ON TV]

838
01:07:31,269 --> 01:07:32,497
[GROANS]

839
01:07:35,206 --> 01:07:38,198
[GRUNTING AND GROANING]

840
01:07:48,352 --> 01:07:51,344
[SCREAMING]

841
01:07:59,664 --> 01:08:02,155
[GRUNTING]

842
01:08:02,333 --> 01:08:05,325
<i>What happened tonight took place
in just a matter of seconds...</i>

843
01:08:05,503 --> 01:08:08,199
<i>... but people will be talking about it
for years to come.</i>

844
01:08:08,372 --> 01:08:12,274
<i>A helicopter careening out of control,
headed toward certain tragedy...</i>

845
01:08:12,443 --> 01:08:16,607
<i>... when all of a sudden, a mystery man,
a hero, saves the day...</i>

846
01:08:16,781 --> 01:08:20,376
<i>... incredibly diverting the helicopter
from destroying innocent people...</i>

847
01:08:20,585 --> 01:08:24,885
<i>... and miraculously rescuing Carol Ferris.</i>

848
01:08:25,323 --> 01:08:30,522
<i>The real question tonight is who is this
amazing hero and where is he now?</i>

849
01:08:30,695 --> 01:08:31,719
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

850
01:08:31,896 --> 01:08:33,227
[GRUNTS]

851
01:08:33,397 --> 01:08:35,729
[GROANS]

852
01:08:35,900 --> 01:08:38,164
[KNOCKING CONTINUES]

853
01:08:40,872 --> 01:08:42,931
Start talking.

854
01:08:44,108 --> 01:08:45,575
- A racetrack?
- Yeah.

855
01:08:45,743 --> 01:08:47,142
TOM:
Hmm.

856
01:08:47,311 --> 01:08:50,747
That's the best you could come up with
for your first big appearance? Racetrack.

857
01:08:50,915 --> 01:08:53,076
Oh, I'm sorry. Did I disappoint you?

858
01:08:53,251 --> 01:08:57,847
I materialized a track out of pure energy,
saving hundreds, and you're disappointed.

859
01:08:58,022 --> 01:08:59,148
I'm sorry about that.

860
01:08:59,323 --> 01:09:01,018
No, I wanna see this stuff. Show me.

861
01:09:01,192 --> 01:09:02,750
I don't think that's a good idea.

862
01:09:02,927 --> 01:09:04,451
Come on, I wanna see this stuff.

863
01:09:04,629 --> 01:09:07,257
I wanna see the outfit, the flying...
You gotta show me.

864
01:09:07,431 --> 01:09:09,296
Hal, being your best friend's no picnic.

865
01:09:09,467 --> 01:09:11,697
- It's for emergencies!
- You owe me!

866
01:09:12,503 --> 01:09:15,165
Hal, I wanna see it.

867
01:09:16,374 --> 01:09:17,398
Fine.

868
01:09:18,743 --> 01:09:20,210
Hold on to your glasses.

869
01:09:20,978 --> 01:09:22,343
[CHUCKLES]

870
01:09:22,947 --> 01:09:24,175
HAL:
All right.

871
01:09:24,348 --> 01:09:25,838
Question:

872
01:09:26,951 --> 01:09:29,681
- You ready to have your mind blown?
- Yeah.

873
01:09:30,621 --> 01:09:31,815
Ring.

874
01:09:31,989 --> 01:09:33,547
Finger.

875
01:09:40,631 --> 01:09:41,791
[EXHALES]

876
01:09:44,068 --> 01:09:45,228
Here we go.

877
01:09:45,403 --> 01:09:46,495
[GRUNTS]

878
01:09:52,810 --> 01:09:56,007
- Did you break it already?
- I didn't break it, okay? It's just...

879
01:09:56,180 --> 01:09:58,910
It's out of juice. I have to recharge it.

880
01:10:09,193 --> 01:10:11,024
Now pay attention.

881
01:10:14,298 --> 01:10:15,993
Aah! Green!

882
01:10:18,636 --> 01:10:21,127
- Wow.
- I know, right?!

883
01:10:21,305 --> 01:10:23,796
[LAUGHS]

884
01:10:23,975 --> 01:10:25,499
Whoo!

885
01:10:25,676 --> 01:10:28,440
[LAUGHING]

886
01:10:28,613 --> 01:10:29,773
Not bad, huh?

887
01:10:29,947 --> 01:10:32,108
You're a superhero.

888
01:10:32,650 --> 01:10:35,642
[TOM LAUGHING]

889
01:10:40,424 --> 01:10:42,324
Don't they always get the girl?

890
01:11:11,322 --> 01:11:12,949
Evening, ma'am.

891
01:11:13,624 --> 01:11:16,252
Didn't get a chance to say goodbye.

892
01:11:16,894 --> 01:11:18,589
Are you okay?

893
01:11:18,763 --> 01:11:22,221
Uh, yeah, no,
I'm glad to have a chance to thank you.

894
01:11:22,400 --> 01:11:25,130
Just doing my job.
No thanks necessary, miss.

895
01:11:25,569 --> 01:11:27,400
No, it is.

896
01:11:28,139 --> 01:11:30,004
You saved my life.

897
01:11:30,408 --> 01:11:33,536
You saved all of our lives.
That was a very...

898
01:11:40,818 --> 01:11:41,978
Hal?

899
01:11:42,420 --> 01:11:43,546
Miss?

900
01:11:43,721 --> 01:11:45,154
Hal?!

901
01:11:45,923 --> 01:11:48,585
Oh, my Go... Oh, my God!

902
01:11:48,793 --> 01:11:51,421
- Oh, my God! Hal!
- How did you know it was me?

903
01:11:51,595 --> 01:11:54,325
What? I've known you my whole life!
I've seen you naked!

904
01:11:54,498 --> 01:11:57,433
You don't think I would recognize you
because I can't see your cheekbones?!

905
01:11:57,601 --> 01:12:01,332
What is this?! Why is your skin green?
Why are you glowing?

906
01:12:01,505 --> 01:12:03,200
What the hell is with that mask?!

907
01:12:03,808 --> 01:12:04,934
It came with the outfit.

908
01:12:07,278 --> 01:12:08,540
Cool, huh?

909
01:12:09,880 --> 01:12:13,111
CAROL: So it all works
because of this magic ring? Ha, ha.

910
01:12:13,284 --> 01:12:15,946
HAL:
No, there's no such thing as magic.

911
01:12:16,120 --> 01:12:18,714
Intergalactic green peacekeepers,
thousands of them.

912
01:12:18,889 --> 01:12:21,187
CAROL: Ha, ha.
- But, no.

913
01:12:21,459 --> 01:12:22,551
I'm not making it up.

914
01:12:22,727 --> 01:12:24,490
[CAROL LAUGHS]

915
01:12:25,096 --> 01:12:27,564
CAROL: I mean, when we were kids,
who'd have thought?

916
01:12:28,199 --> 01:12:31,691
- I did, actually. I called this early on.
- Ha-ha-ha.

917
01:12:31,869 --> 01:12:35,896
I said, "One day I'll be a green space cop."
Here I am.

918
01:12:37,708 --> 01:12:41,144
Okay, so at the party, how did you
make that big green ramp thing?

919
01:12:41,879 --> 01:12:45,212
Anything I see in my mind, I can create.
I just have to focus.

920
01:12:45,883 --> 01:12:46,941
Anything?

921
01:12:47,952 --> 01:12:49,214
Anything.

922
01:12:52,223 --> 01:12:55,158
[CAROL GASPING]

923
01:13:04,435 --> 01:13:07,563
Happy birthday. Better late than never.

924
01:13:08,773 --> 01:13:09,831
Um...

925
01:13:10,841 --> 01:13:12,502
Okay, so how does it work?

926
01:13:12,676 --> 01:13:17,943
They just, um, call you on your cell,
"Cat in a tree, downtown Milky Way"?

927
01:13:18,115 --> 01:13:21,175
No. I don't think it works
exactly like that.

928
01:13:21,352 --> 01:13:23,912
Well, technically speaking, um...

929
01:13:24,155 --> 01:13:26,316
...I actually sort of, uh...

930
01:13:27,391 --> 01:13:28,619
...quit.

931
01:13:28,793 --> 01:13:30,021
What do you mean? How?

932
01:13:30,194 --> 01:13:33,686
Well, I mean, it's a lot like quitting
anything else, really.

933
01:13:34,298 --> 01:13:35,526
I don't understand.

934
01:13:35,699 --> 01:13:37,963
How do you walk away
from something like that?

935
01:13:38,135 --> 01:13:39,329
Is that even possible?

936
01:13:39,503 --> 01:13:42,961
Oh, I think we both know
I'm pretty good at walking away.

937
01:13:47,912 --> 01:13:51,370
If for once you didn't quit something
you cared about...

938
01:13:51,549 --> 01:13:53,779
...what's the worst that could happen?

939
01:14:11,168 --> 01:14:13,398
Well, thank you.
This has been really something.

940
01:14:13,571 --> 01:14:16,938
- I know I've made a lot of mistakes...
- Look, Hal, I'm not mad at you.

941
01:14:17,842 --> 01:14:20,037
I feel bad for you, really.

942
01:14:20,377 --> 01:14:23,210
You've been given so much so often.

943
01:14:24,081 --> 01:14:25,548
And you just...

944
01:14:29,887 --> 01:14:31,514
Good night.

945
01:15:01,852 --> 01:15:04,844
[WHEEZING]

946
01:15:19,103 --> 01:15:20,900
[CHUCKLES]

947
01:15:21,639 --> 01:15:22,867
[DOOR OPENS]

948
01:15:24,008 --> 01:15:25,032
WALLER:
Dr. Hammond?

949
01:15:27,378 --> 01:15:30,245
There is something I'd like to show you.

950
01:15:30,414 --> 01:15:33,850
Something I'm fairly certain
you'll want to see.

951
01:15:42,126 --> 01:15:43,423
<i>SON:
See you later, Mom.</i>

952
01:15:43,594 --> 01:15:45,255
<i>DAUGHTER: I love you.
JOSEPH: Bye, baby.</i>

953
01:15:45,429 --> 01:15:46,862
[GUNFIRE]

954
01:15:47,031 --> 01:15:48,896
<i>WALLER:
No!</i>

955
01:15:49,800 --> 01:15:51,233
[WALLER SOBBING]

956
01:15:51,969 --> 01:15:56,338
Physical contact
accesses mnemonic data.

957
01:15:56,974 --> 01:15:59,738
I can see your memories.

958
01:15:59,910 --> 01:16:01,571
[HECTOR CHUCKLES]

959
01:16:03,280 --> 01:16:04,804
[CHUCKLING]

960
01:16:36,146 --> 01:16:37,170
Dad.

961
01:16:38,849 --> 01:16:41,181
Son, this is my fault.

962
01:16:42,019 --> 01:16:43,782
But I'm gonna fix it.

963
01:16:44,688 --> 01:16:48,146
We're gonna get you well again.
Whatever it takes.

964
01:16:49,960 --> 01:16:52,724
I don't know what you're talking about.

965
01:16:52,896 --> 01:16:55,296
We detected traces
of a second alien life form...

966
01:16:55,466 --> 01:16:57,559
...buried within the body of the first.

967
01:16:57,735 --> 01:17:00,067
You've been exposed.

968
01:17:00,404 --> 01:17:05,341
I've never felt better in my life.

969
01:17:06,110 --> 01:17:08,476
We know everything, son.

970
01:17:09,213 --> 01:17:11,579
I've never felt better in my life.

971
01:17:11,749 --> 01:17:14,741
[HECTOR GRUNTING]

972
01:17:31,902 --> 01:17:35,668
<i>TOMAR-RE: To be chosen to join its ranks
is the highest of honors...</i>

973
01:17:35,839 --> 01:17:38,364
<i>... and the greatest of responsibilities.</i>

974
01:17:38,609 --> 01:17:41,077
<i>The ring never makes a mistake.</i>

975
01:17:42,212 --> 01:17:43,907
[BEEPING]

976
01:18:00,197 --> 01:18:03,189
[GRUNTING]

977
01:18:06,136 --> 01:18:07,763
HAMMOND:
It's gonna be all right.

978
01:18:07,938 --> 01:18:10,372
They just need to run some tests,
that's all.

979
01:18:15,712 --> 01:18:17,202
Keep him under.

980
01:18:20,484 --> 01:18:22,577
I only want what's best for you.

981
01:18:32,629 --> 01:18:35,291
[GRUNTING]

982
01:18:41,338 --> 01:18:42,566
Run.

983
01:18:43,006 --> 01:18:44,769
[ALARM BLARING]

984
01:18:44,942 --> 01:18:47,843
[BOTH GRUNTING]

985
01:18:49,146 --> 01:18:50,340
[BLOWS]

986
01:18:50,514 --> 01:18:51,947
[SCREAMS THEN GRUNTS]

987
01:18:54,952 --> 01:18:57,318
[YELLING]

988
01:19:03,293 --> 01:19:04,351
[BOTH SCREAM]

989
01:19:09,533 --> 01:19:12,331
[GUARDS GRUNTING]

990
01:19:17,641 --> 01:19:19,472
- Hector.
HECTOR: Shh, shh.

991
01:19:19,643 --> 01:19:21,167
Don't worry.

992
01:19:23,013 --> 01:19:25,004
I only want what's best for you.

993
01:19:26,817 --> 01:19:28,512
[CHUCKLING]

994
01:19:33,524 --> 01:19:34,650
[GASPS]

995
01:19:35,526 --> 01:19:36,686
[WALLER GROANS]

996
01:19:41,165 --> 01:19:42,894
[WALLER GROANS]

997
01:19:57,881 --> 01:20:00,850
[HECTOR SCREAMING]

998
01:20:04,588 --> 01:20:05,680
[GRUNTING]

999
01:20:06,657 --> 01:20:09,820
[ROARING]

1000
01:20:09,993 --> 01:20:12,484
[GRUNTING]

1001
01:20:30,280 --> 01:20:33,272
[BOTH PANTING]

1002
01:20:35,152 --> 01:20:38,144
[LAUGHING]

1003
01:20:47,197 --> 01:20:49,688
The ring, it chose you.

1004
01:20:49,866 --> 01:20:51,390
Take it!

1005
01:20:53,203 --> 01:20:54,534
HECTOR:
Hal.

1006
01:20:55,405 --> 01:20:57,202
Hi.

1007
01:20:57,374 --> 01:20:59,934
[LAUGHING]

1008
01:21:00,110 --> 01:21:02,943
The alien was one of you.

1009
01:21:04,915 --> 01:21:07,475
How did we end up so different?

1010
01:21:07,651 --> 01:21:09,380
Hmm? Hmm?

1011
01:21:09,553 --> 01:21:11,180
Sit down!

1012
01:21:11,355 --> 01:21:12,822
[HECTOR HARRUMPHS]

1013
01:21:13,457 --> 01:21:14,719
Now...

1014
01:21:16,927 --> 01:21:18,155
...how's Carol?

1015
01:21:20,297 --> 01:21:21,764
- That came out wrong.
- Please.

1016
01:21:21,932 --> 01:21:23,797
HAL: I've made mistakes...
- Look, Hal...

1017
01:21:23,967 --> 01:21:26,435
I feel bad for you, really. Good night.

1018
01:21:26,603 --> 01:21:29,595
[HECTOR PANTING]

1019
01:21:32,276 --> 01:21:36,542
You're just as much of a failure
as I was.

1020
01:21:37,848 --> 01:21:39,475
And just as afraid.

1021
01:21:40,717 --> 01:21:43,117
Well...

1022
01:21:43,854 --> 01:21:46,084
...I used to fight my fear.

1023
01:21:49,826 --> 01:21:53,990
But now that I've tasted its true power...

1024
01:21:57,601 --> 01:21:59,660
...I'll never go back.

1025
01:21:59,836 --> 01:22:02,999
[YELLING]

1026
01:22:06,476 --> 01:22:07,773
[SCREAMING]

1027
01:22:08,178 --> 01:22:10,146
HAL:
No!

1028
01:22:17,788 --> 01:22:20,780
[GRUNTING]

1029
01:22:23,760 --> 01:22:25,227
[YELLING]

1030
01:22:29,833 --> 01:22:33,462
You wear the ring of the Lantern
that imprisoned me.

1031
01:22:34,371 --> 01:22:36,839
<i>You will suffer the same fate.</i>

1032
01:22:37,007 --> 01:22:40,340
Once I have devoured your world...

1033
01:22:40,510 --> 01:22:42,842
<i>... I will have all the strength I need...</i>

1034
01:22:43,013 --> 01:22:46,881
...to defeat the Corps
and destroy the Guardians.

1035
01:22:51,054 --> 01:22:54,046
[HECTOR YELLING]

1036
01:22:56,927 --> 01:22:59,919
[SCREAMING]

1037
01:23:19,249 --> 01:23:20,580
TOM:
Let me get this straight.

1038
01:23:20,751 --> 01:23:24,152
This thing that's out there attacking planets
is connected to Hector?

1039
01:23:24,321 --> 01:23:26,881
Somehow it infected him
after it killed Abin Sur.

1040
01:23:27,057 --> 01:23:31,289
- Well, you're just gonna have to stop it.
- Oh, I'm just gonna have to stop it, huh?

1041
01:23:31,461 --> 01:23:33,122
Well, I tried that and I failed.

1042
01:23:33,296 --> 01:23:36,595
And the senator died.
I told you, the ring made a mistake.

1043
01:23:36,767 --> 01:23:39,429
Wait, go back.
How did the ring make a mistake?

1044
01:23:39,603 --> 01:23:44,563
The one thing that a Green Lantern
is supposed to be is fearless.

1045
01:23:45,108 --> 01:23:48,236
Fearless is the job description.

1046
01:23:48,879 --> 01:23:49,903
That isn't me.

1047
01:23:50,080 --> 01:23:52,446
So you're just gonna walk away again?

1048
01:23:52,616 --> 01:23:56,552
Explain this to me, Hal.
Please explain to me just once, why.

1049
01:23:56,720 --> 01:23:58,483
Because I'm afraid!

1050
01:24:15,272 --> 01:24:17,331
You don't think your dad ever felt afraid?

1051
01:24:18,608 --> 01:24:20,439
If he did,
he figured out some way to beat it.

1052
01:24:20,610 --> 01:24:23,340
Yeah, well, there's a word for that:

1053
01:24:23,647 --> 01:24:25,205
Courage.

1054
01:24:32,122 --> 01:24:35,819
They said that the ring wouldn't have
chosen me if it didn't see something.

1055
01:24:36,860 --> 01:24:40,125
Something I don't see. Yet.

1056
01:24:43,867 --> 01:24:45,232
I see it.

1057
01:24:46,570 --> 01:24:48,538
I always have.

1058
01:24:49,439 --> 01:24:51,873
The ring didn't see
that you were fearless.

1059
01:24:52,042 --> 01:24:55,341
It saw that you had the ability to
overcome fear.

1060
01:24:56,112 --> 01:24:58,512
It saw that you're courageous.

1061
01:25:01,685 --> 01:25:03,016
Which you are.

1062
01:25:03,887 --> 01:25:05,184
Just like your dad.

1063
01:25:09,860 --> 01:25:12,852
[GRUNTING]

1064
01:25:13,864 --> 01:25:16,594
<i>PARALLAX:
The Lantern is a threat.</i>

1065
01:25:17,467 --> 01:25:19,765
<i>Eliminate him.</i>

1066
01:25:53,737 --> 01:25:55,864
SINESTRO:
Our new weapon is ready.

1067
01:25:56,573 --> 01:25:58,268
Once I've mastered its power...

1068
01:25:58,909 --> 01:26:01,571
...I'll begin training the Corps
to do the same.

1069
01:26:02,946 --> 01:26:05,073
Though Earth will be lost...

1070
01:26:05,515 --> 01:26:09,576
...we'll be ready to make a stand against
Parallax before it reaches Oa.

1071
01:26:09,753 --> 01:26:11,345
Then the power of the enemy
will be ours.

1072
01:26:11,521 --> 01:26:13,352
HAL:
At what cost?

1073
01:26:16,126 --> 01:26:18,788
SINESTRO: You dare enter this chamber?
- I need your help.

1074
01:26:20,397 --> 01:26:22,592
You gotta help me save my world.

1075
01:26:30,440 --> 01:26:35,639
I know that humans aren't the strongest
species, or the smartest.

1076
01:26:37,047 --> 01:26:39,140
We're young, we have a lot to learn.

1077
01:26:39,849 --> 01:26:41,146
But we're worth saving.

1078
01:26:49,859 --> 01:26:52,157
This new weapon of yours,
you can't use it.

1079
01:26:52,362 --> 01:26:57,026
Once you cross that line, once you've given
in to fear, you'll never go back. I've seen it.

1080
01:26:58,268 --> 01:27:01,101
Look, I know right now you're afraid.

1081
01:27:01,271 --> 01:27:03,603
You dare accuse the Guardians
of feeling fear?

1082
01:27:03,773 --> 01:27:05,070
Yes, I do.

1083
01:27:05,241 --> 01:27:07,402
That's exactly why Parallax
is beating you...

1084
01:27:07,577 --> 01:27:10,171
...because you're afraid
to even admit you're afraid.

1085
01:27:10,347 --> 01:27:11,905
I know.

1086
01:27:12,315 --> 01:27:14,283
I spent my entire life doing it.

1087
01:27:15,518 --> 01:27:18,078
You know, we have a saying on Earth.

1088
01:27:18,254 --> 01:27:20,779
We say, "I'm only human."

1089
01:27:22,525 --> 01:27:26,120
We say it because we're vulnerable,
we say it because we know we're afraid.

1090
01:27:26,296 --> 01:27:28,423
It doesn't mean we're weak.

1091
01:27:30,667 --> 01:27:32,134
Help me save my planet.

1092
01:27:33,203 --> 01:27:34,602
Don't give in to fear.

1093
01:27:34,771 --> 01:27:37,899
Fight it. Fight it with me.

1094
01:27:39,142 --> 01:27:41,508
GUARDIAN:
Your words are compelling, young human.

1095
01:27:41,678 --> 01:27:45,341
But as immortals, we must measure
our actions over billions of years...

1096
01:27:45,515 --> 01:27:47,676
...and the fate of the universe.

1097
01:27:47,851 --> 01:27:52,379
We simply cannot risk losing everything
on the chance you might be right.

1098
01:27:52,555 --> 01:27:55,649
Then don't. Don't risk any more lives.

1099
01:27:56,860 --> 01:27:57,986
Just mine.

1100
01:27:59,796 --> 01:28:01,559
Let me go fight for my world...

1101
01:28:01,731 --> 01:28:05,929
...and I'll show you
that will is stronger than fear.

1102
01:28:06,870 --> 01:28:09,065
There is no way you can succeed.

1103
01:28:09,239 --> 01:28:11,434
You will die, Hal Jordan.

1104
01:28:13,043 --> 01:28:15,307
Then I'll die trying.

1105
01:28:17,881 --> 01:28:20,076
Good luck, Green Lantern.

1106
01:28:31,895 --> 01:28:33,226
[RING BEEPING]

1107
01:29:19,409 --> 01:29:20,933
I wouldn't do that.

1108
01:29:23,980 --> 01:29:25,277
Look closely.

1109
01:29:30,253 --> 01:29:32,050
She's beautiful, isn't she?

1110
01:29:33,289 --> 01:29:36,156
I loved her from the moment
I first saw her.

1111
01:29:36,326 --> 01:29:39,489
But she could never see me,
as you were always standing in the way.

1112
01:29:39,662 --> 01:29:41,493
But not anymore.

1113
01:29:42,098 --> 01:29:44,589
No! No! Don't! Don't do this, Hector.

1114
01:29:44,768 --> 01:29:46,292
Please.

1115
01:29:46,970 --> 01:29:48,335
Please.

1116
01:29:49,405 --> 01:29:50,429
I know how you feel.

1117
01:29:50,607 --> 01:29:52,302
[SCOFFS]

1118
01:29:52,475 --> 01:29:54,500
Come on, look at yourself!

1119
01:29:57,180 --> 01:29:59,341
No, I know what it's like...

1120
01:30:00,650 --> 01:30:02,481
...to not live up to expectations...

1121
01:30:02,652 --> 01:30:05,917
...to feel like nothing that you do
will ever be good enough.

1122
01:30:10,193 --> 01:30:12,525
I know what it's like to be afraid.

1123
01:30:13,630 --> 01:30:15,427
Let me help you.

1124
01:30:16,800 --> 01:30:19,667
Hal. You've changed.

1125
01:30:20,937 --> 01:30:24,429
How wonderful that all it took for you
to grow up was the end of the world.

1126
01:30:25,942 --> 01:30:27,637
Now it's my turn.

1127
01:30:29,813 --> 01:30:32,976
And if I can't be like you,
I'm gonna make her like me.

1128
01:30:33,149 --> 01:30:35,310
And let's face it, once she's like me...

1129
01:30:36,119 --> 01:30:38,280
...then you wouldn't be very interested.

1130
01:30:38,454 --> 01:30:40,513
Hmm? Now, would you?

1131
01:30:42,358 --> 01:30:44,485
- Why can't you?
- Hmm?

1132
01:30:45,862 --> 01:30:47,659
Why can't you be like me?

1133
01:30:47,831 --> 01:30:49,856
Heh. Huh?

1134
01:30:51,134 --> 01:30:52,499
Let her go...

1135
01:30:55,872 --> 01:30:56,998
...and you can have it.

1136
01:31:02,745 --> 01:31:04,542
You can do anything.

1137
01:31:05,248 --> 01:31:06,909
Be anything.

1138
01:31:09,552 --> 01:31:10,985
Take it.

1139
01:31:14,290 --> 01:31:16,520
Let her make the choice.

1140
01:31:22,031 --> 01:31:23,498
Okay.

1141
01:31:40,550 --> 01:31:42,916
[HECTOR GASPING]

1142
01:31:51,127 --> 01:31:52,458
Wow.

1143
01:31:55,932 --> 01:31:58,526
[LAUGHING]

1144
01:32:03,072 --> 01:32:04,471
Now bring her down.

1145
01:32:05,408 --> 01:32:06,773
[SIGHS]

1146
01:32:08,111 --> 01:32:09,271
Hal.

1147
01:32:11,080 --> 01:32:12,138
I lied.

1148
01:32:18,221 --> 01:32:19,745
I lied too.

1149
01:32:20,490 --> 01:32:22,458
See, the way it works is...

1150
01:32:22,625 --> 01:32:23,887
...you have to be chosen.

1151
01:32:25,128 --> 01:32:26,618
[SCREAMS]

1152
01:32:26,796 --> 01:32:29,731
[GRUNTING]

1153
01:32:33,303 --> 01:32:34,668
[BOTH GRUNT]

1154
01:32:41,277 --> 01:32:42,767
[GASPS]

1155
01:32:42,946 --> 01:32:45,346
[ROARING]

1156
01:32:49,085 --> 01:32:51,246
[SCREAMING]

1157
01:33:04,634 --> 01:33:06,602
You have failed me.

1158
01:33:06,769 --> 01:33:09,761
[HECTOR SCREAMING]

1159
01:33:38,134 --> 01:33:39,362
Stay here.

1160
01:33:39,535 --> 01:33:40,900
No problem.

1161
01:33:45,375 --> 01:33:48,640
[GRUNTING]

1162
01:34:01,157 --> 01:34:04,183
[HAL YELLING]

1163
01:34:08,498 --> 01:34:11,490
Your will is strong,
but not strong enough.

1164
01:34:12,602 --> 01:34:15,400
You are nothing without the ring.

1165
01:34:15,571 --> 01:34:17,004
[HAL YELLING]

1166
01:34:24,347 --> 01:34:26,941
[PARALLAX ROARS]

1167
01:34:41,297 --> 01:34:43,788
<i>POLICEMAN [OVER LOUDSPEAKER]:
You must move out of the area now.</i>

1168
01:34:43,966 --> 01:34:46,434
<i>Please clear the streets.</i>

1169
01:34:46,602 --> 01:34:48,399
<i>Clear the streets immediately.</i>

1170
01:34:51,874 --> 01:34:54,104
You can never beat this. You'll die.

1171
01:34:54,277 --> 01:34:56,108
At least I can get it away from here.

1172
01:34:56,279 --> 01:34:58,941
- How do you think you're gonna do that?
- I don't know. I don't know.

1173
01:34:59,115 --> 01:35:00,207
[STAMMERS]

1174
01:35:00,383 --> 01:35:02,817
Maybe I can outthink it or...

1175
01:35:02,985 --> 01:35:04,816
The dogfight, remember?

1176
01:35:04,987 --> 01:35:06,477
Those were a couple of jets.

1177
01:35:06,656 --> 01:35:08,749
Unbeatable jets.

1178
01:35:11,060 --> 01:35:13,620
The ring chose me for a reason.

1179
01:35:14,897 --> 01:35:16,694
This is why.

1180
01:35:18,267 --> 01:35:21,134
- Look, I'm probably not...
- Please don't. No.

1181
01:35:21,304 --> 01:35:22,703
Hey.

1182
01:35:22,872 --> 01:35:25,340
[CAROL CRYING]

1183
01:35:31,747 --> 01:35:33,977
<i>POLICEMAN [OVER LOUDSPEAKER]:
This is a mandatory evacuation.</i>

1184
01:35:34,150 --> 01:35:36,482
<i>Everyone must clear the streets
immediately.</i>

1185
01:35:38,087 --> 01:35:42,148
<i>Police emergency,
everyone must clear the street now.</i>

1186
01:35:42,492 --> 01:35:44,119
[CROWD GASPING]

1187
01:35:46,529 --> 01:35:49,521
[CROWD SCREAMING AND SHOUTING]

1188
01:36:17,460 --> 01:36:19,894
DRIVER:
Everybody off now! Now!

1189
01:36:20,429 --> 01:36:21,657
Go! Go!

1190
01:36:31,007 --> 01:36:32,338
MAN:
Run!

1191
01:36:35,711 --> 01:36:37,201
[DRIVER SCREAMS]

1192
01:36:41,717 --> 01:36:43,048
[SCREAMS]

1193
01:36:52,161 --> 01:36:53,628
[ROARS]

1194
01:36:56,766 --> 01:36:57,858
[SCREAMS]

1195
01:36:58,901 --> 01:37:00,493
- Run!
- Aah! Aah!

1196
01:37:02,238 --> 01:37:05,173
[GRUNTING]

1197
01:37:08,744 --> 01:37:12,180
[CAR ALARM BLARING]

1198
01:37:13,015 --> 01:37:14,448
[ROARS]

1199
01:37:19,222 --> 01:37:21,952
I feel your fear growing.

1200
01:37:22,358 --> 01:37:24,155
You will be dead soon.

1201
01:37:24,327 --> 01:37:27,125
In brightest day, in blackest night...

1202
01:37:27,296 --> 01:37:30,754
And when you're gone,
I'll destroy everything you ever loved.

1203
01:37:30,933 --> 01:37:33,925
- No evil shall escape my sight.

1204
01:37:34,103 --> 01:37:37,561
Your family, your home,
your planet will be no more.

1205
01:37:38,007 --> 01:37:41,875
Let those who worship evil's might...

1206
01:37:42,044 --> 01:37:46,674
The entire human race will be wiped out
because you, Hal Jordan...

1207
01:37:46,849 --> 01:37:48,373
...were afraid.

1208
01:37:48,551 --> 01:37:51,076
- Beware my power:

1209
01:37:51,621 --> 01:37:52,952
Green Lantern's light!

1210
01:37:53,623 --> 01:37:56,990
[PARALLAX ROARING]

1211
01:39:08,964 --> 01:39:12,866
The bigger you are, the faster you burn.

1212
01:39:35,024 --> 01:39:36,855
[ROARING]

1213
01:40:23,806 --> 01:40:25,706
[SCREAMS]

1214
01:41:14,490 --> 01:41:16,958
<i>SINESTRO: Though his time
wearing the ring has been brief...</i>

1215
01:41:18,060 --> 01:41:23,327
...Hal Jordan's defeat of Parallax will be
remembered as long as the Corps exists.

1216
01:41:23,566 --> 01:41:27,195
His actions are a reminder
of why the ring chose each of us.

1217
01:41:28,337 --> 01:41:30,168
To overcome fear...

1218
01:41:30,873 --> 01:41:34,172
...and destroy evil wherever it may hide.

1219
01:41:42,751 --> 01:41:44,981
As Lanterns,
we must fight with all our will.

1220
01:41:46,755 --> 01:41:49,189
Our wills haven't always been united.

1221
01:41:51,026 --> 01:41:52,288
It's time they were.

1222
01:41:52,895 --> 01:41:54,157
[GRUNTS]

1223
01:41:54,330 --> 01:41:56,958
- Ha-ha-ha.
- Can I train them or can I train them?

1224
01:41:58,200 --> 01:42:00,600
SINESTRO:
You're impertinent, Hal Jordan.

1225
01:42:00,769 --> 01:42:04,398
You're rash, volatile, opinionated.

1226
01:42:05,875 --> 01:42:09,140
It seems Abin Sur found another
just like himself.

1227
01:42:21,090 --> 01:42:24,082
[LANTERNS CHEERING]

1228
01:42:51,086 --> 01:42:54,021
Wow, I am never getting used to that.

1229
01:42:58,594 --> 01:43:02,086
My new job requires that I travel.

1230
01:43:02,565 --> 01:43:03,589
[CHUCKLES]

1231
01:43:04,934 --> 01:43:06,367
Be away for a while.

1232
01:43:10,205 --> 01:43:13,936
Away, never gone.

1233
01:43:18,714 --> 01:43:19,908
Hal.

1234
01:43:20,082 --> 01:43:21,413
Yeah?

1235
01:43:21,784 --> 01:43:23,945
Can you take off the mask?

1236
01:43:29,124 --> 01:43:30,455
That's really cool. Ha, ha.

1237
01:43:42,471 --> 01:43:43,665
[CAROL SIGHS]

1238
01:43:45,174 --> 01:43:47,005
So, what happens now?

1239
01:43:48,243 --> 01:43:50,177
I'm gonna go look for trouble.

1240
01:43:51,914 --> 01:43:53,381
[CAROL CHUCKLES]

1241
01:44:13,702 --> 01:44:16,102
<i>TOMAR-RE: Of all the Lanterns
who have ever worn the ring...</i>

1242
01:44:16,271 --> 01:44:19,263
<i>... there was one
whose light shined brightest.</i>

1243
01:44:19,708 --> 01:44:23,041
<i>At first, his humanity
was thought to be a weakness.</i>

1244
01:44:23,212 --> 01:44:27,114
<i>And yet it proved to be
his greatest strength.</i>

